159 class AddrLabelMapCallbackPtr final : CallbackVH {
160  AddrLabelMap *Map = nullptr;
161 
162 public:
163  AddrLabelMapCallbackPtr() = default;
164  AddrLabelMapCallbackPtr(Value *V) : CallbackVH(V) {}
165 
166  void setPtr(BasicBlock *BB) {
167  ValueHandleBase::operator=(BB);
168  }
169 
170  void setMap(AddrLabelMap *map) { Map = map; }
171 
172  void deleted() override;
173  void allUsesReplacedWith(Value *V2) override;
174 };
175 } // namespace
176 
177 class llvm::AddrLabelMap {
178  MCContext &Context;
179  struct AddrLabelSymEntry {
180  /// The symbols for the label.
181  TinyPtrVector<MCSymbol *> Symbols;
182 
183  Function *Fn; // The containing function of the BasicBlock.
184  unsigned Index; // The index in BBCallbacks for the BasicBlock.
185  };
186 
187  DenseMap<AssertingVH<BasicBlock>, AddrLabelSymEntry> AddrLabelSymbols;
188 
189  /// Callbacks for the BasicBlock's that we have entries for. We use this so
190  /// we get notified if a block is deleted or RAUWd.
191  std::vector<AddrLabelMapCallbackPtr> BBCallbacks;
192 
193  /// This is a per-function list of symbols whose corresponding BasicBlock got
194  /// deleted. These symbols need to be emitted at some point in the file, so
195  /// AsmPrinter emits them after the function body.
196  DenseMap<AssertingVH<Function>, std::vector<MCSymbol *>>
197  DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission;
198 
199 public:
200  AddrLabelMap(MCContext &context) : Context(context) {}
201 
202  ~AddrLabelMap() {
203  assert(DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission.empty() &&
204  "Some labels for deleted blocks never got emitted");
205  }
206 
207  ArrayRef<MCSymbol *> getAddrLabelSymbolToEmit(BasicBlock *BB);
208 
209  void takeDeletedSymbolsForFunction(Function *F,
210  std::vector<MCSymbol *> &Result);
211 
212  void UpdateForDeletedBlock(BasicBlock *BB);
213  void UpdateForRAUWBlock(BasicBlock *Old, BasicBlock *New);
214 };
215 
216 ArrayRef<MCSymbol *> AddrLabelMap::getAddrLabelSymbolToEmit(BasicBlock *BB) {
217  assert(BB->hasAddressTaken() &&
218  "Shouldn't get label for block without address taken");
219  AddrLabelSymEntry &Entry = AddrLabelSymbols[BB];
220 
221  // If we already had an entry for this block, just return it.
222  if (!Entry.Symbols.empty()) {
223  assert(BB->getParent() == Entry.Fn && "Parent changed");
224  return Entry.Symbols;
225  }
226 
227  // Otherwise, this is a new entry, create a new symbol for it and add an
228  // entry to BBCallbacks so we can be notified if the BB is deleted or RAUWd.
229  BBCallbacks.emplace_back(BB);
230  BBCallbacks.back().setMap(this);
231  Entry.Index = BBCallbacks.size() - 1;
232  Entry.Fn = BB->getParent();
233  MCSymbol *Sym = BB->hasAddressTaken() ? Context.createNamedTempSymbol()
234  : Context.createTempSymbol();
235  Entry.Symbols.push_back(Sym);
236  return Entry.Symbols;
237 }
238 
239 /// If we have any deleted symbols for F, return them.
240 void AddrLabelMap::takeDeletedSymbolsForFunction(
241  Function *F, std::vector<MCSymbol *> &Result) {
242  DenseMap<AssertingVH<Function>, std::vector<MCSymbol *>>::iterator I =
243  DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission.find(F);
244 
245  // If there are no entries for the function, just return.
246  if (I == DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission.end())
247  return;
248 
249  // Otherwise, take the list.
250  std::swap(Result, I->second);
251  DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission.erase(I);
252 }
253 
254 //===- Address of Block Management ----------------------------------------===//
255 
256 ArrayRef<MCSymbol *>
257 AsmPrinter::getAddrLabelSymbolToEmit(const BasicBlock *BB) {
258  // Lazily create AddrLabelSymbols.
259  if (!AddrLabelSymbols)
260  AddrLabelSymbols = std::make_unique<AddrLabelMap>(OutContext);
261  return AddrLabelSymbols->getAddrLabelSymbolToEmit(
262  const_cast<BasicBlock *>(BB));
263 }
264 
265 void AsmPrinter::takeDeletedSymbolsForFunction(
266  const Function *F, std::vector<MCSymbol *> &Result) {
267  // If no blocks have had their addresses taken, we're done.
268  if (!AddrLabelSymbols)
269  return;
270  return AddrLabelSymbols->takeDeletedSymbolsForFunction(
271  const_cast<Function *>(F), Result);
272 }
273 
274 void AddrLabelMap::UpdateForDeletedBlock(BasicBlock *BB) {
275  // If the block got deleted, there is no need for the symbol. If the symbol
276  // was already emitted, we can just forget about it, otherwise we need to
277  // queue it up for later emission when the function is output.
278  AddrLabelSymEntry Entry = std::move(AddrLabelSymbols[BB]);
279  AddrLabelSymbols.erase(BB);
280  assert(!Entry.Symbols.empty() && "Didn't have a symbol, why a callback?");
281  BBCallbacks[Entry.Index] = nullptr; // Clear the callback.
282 
283 #if !LLVM_MEMORY_SANITIZER_BUILD
284  // BasicBlock is destroyed already, so this access is UB detectable by msan.
285  assert((BB->getParent() == nullptr || BB->getParent() == Entry.Fn) &&
286  "Block/parent mismatch");
287 #endif
288 
289  for (MCSymbol *Sym : Entry.Symbols) {
290  if (Sym->isDefined())
291  return;
292 
293  // If the block is not yet defined, we need to emit it at the end of the
294  // function. Add the symbol to the DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission list
295  // for the containing Function. Since the block is being deleted, its
296  // parent may already be removed, we have to get the function from 'Entry'.
297  DeletedAddrLabelsNeedingEmission[Entry.Fn].push_back(Sym);
298  }
299 }
300 
301 void AddrLabelMap::UpdateForRAUWBlock(BasicBlock *Old, BasicBlock *New) {
302  // Get the entry for the RAUW'd block and remove it from our map.
303  AddrLabelSymEntry OldEntry = std::move(AddrLabelSymbols[Old]);
304  AddrLabelSymbols.erase(Old);
305  assert(!OldEntry.Symbols.empty() && "Didn't have a symbol, why a callback?");
306 
307  AddrLabelSymEntry &NewEntry = AddrLabelSymbols[New];
308 
309  // If New is not address taken, just move our symbol over to it.
310  if (NewEntry.Symbols.empty()) {
311  BBCallbacks[OldEntry.Index].setPtr(New); // Update the callback.
312  NewEntry = std::move(OldEntry); // Set New's entry.
313  return;
314  }
315 
316  BBCallbacks[OldEntry.Index] = nullptr; // Update the callback.
317 
318  // Otherwise, we need to add the old symbols to the new block's set.
319  llvm::append_range(NewEntry.Symbols, OldEntry.Symbols);
320 }
321 
322 void AddrLabelMapCallbackPtr::deleted() {
323  Map->UpdateForDeletedBlock(cast<BasicBlock>(getValPtr()));
324 }
325 
326 void AddrLabelMapCallbackPtr::allUsesReplacedWith(Value *V2) {
327  Map->UpdateForRAUWBlock(cast<BasicBlock>(getValPtr()), cast<BasicBlock>(V2));
328 }

330 /// getGVAlignment - Return the alignment to use for the specified global
331 /// value. This rounds up to the preferred alignment if possible and legal.
332 Align AsmPrinter::getGVAlignment(const GlobalObject *GV, const DataLayout &DL,
333  Align InAlign) {
334  Align Alignment;
335  if (const GlobalVariable *GVar = dyn_cast<GlobalVariable>(GV))
336  Alignment = DL.getPreferredAlign(GVar);
337 
338  // If InAlign is specified, round it to it.
339  if (InAlign > Alignment)
340  Alignment = InAlign;
341 
342  // If the GV has a specified alignment, take it into account.
343  const MaybeAlign GVAlign(GV->getAlign());
344  if (!GVAlign)
345  return Alignment;
346 
347  assert(GVAlign && "GVAlign must be set");
348 
349  // If the GVAlign is larger than NumBits, or if we are required to obey
350  // NumBits because the GV has an assigned section, obey it.
351  if (*GVAlign > Alignment || GV->hasSection())
352  Alignment = *GVAlign;
353  return Alignment;
354 }

402 void AsmPrinter::emitInitialRawDwarfLocDirective(const MachineFunction &MF) {
403  if (DD) {
404  assert(OutStreamer->hasRawTextSupport() &&
405  "Expected assembly output mode.");
406  // This is NVPTX specific and it's unclear why.
407  // PR51079: If we have code without debug information we need to give up.
408  DISubprogram *MFSP = MF.getFunction().getSubprogram();
409  if (!MFSP)
410  return;
411  (void)DD->emitInitialLocDirective(MF, /*CUID=*/0);
412  }
413 }

428 bool AsmPrinter::doInitialization(Module &M) {
429  auto *MMIWP = getAnalysisIfAvailable<MachineModuleInfoWrapperPass>();
430  MMI = MMIWP ? &MMIWP->getMMI() : nullptr;
431  HasSplitStack = false;
432  HasNoSplitStack = false;
433 
434  AddrLabelSymbols = nullptr;
435 
436  // Initialize TargetLoweringObjectFile.
437  const_cast<TargetLoweringObjectFile&>(getObjFileLowering())
438  .Initialize(OutContext, TM);
439 
440  const_cast<TargetLoweringObjectFile &>(getObjFileLowering())
441  .getModuleMetadata(M);
442 
443  OutStreamer->initSections(false, *TM.getMCSubtargetInfo());
444 
445  // Emit the version-min deployment target directive if needed.
446  //
447  // FIXME: If we end up with a collection of these sorts of Darwin-specific
448  // or ELF-specific things, it may make sense to have a platform helper class
449  // that will work with the target helper class. For now keep it here, as the
450  // alternative is duplicated code in each of the target asm printers that
451  // use the directive, where it would need the same conditionalization
452  // anyway.
453  const Triple &Target = TM.getTargetTriple();
454  Triple TVT(M.getDarwinTargetVariantTriple());
455  OutStreamer->emitVersionForTarget(
456  Target, M.getSDKVersion(),
457  M.getDarwinTargetVariantTriple().empty() ? nullptr : &TVT,
458  M.getDarwinTargetVariantSDKVersion());
459 
460  // Allow the target to emit any magic that it wants at the start of the file.
461  emitStartOfAsmFile(M);
462 
463  // Very minimal debug info. It is ignored if we emit actual debug info. If we
464  // don't, this at least helps the user find where a global came from.
465  if (MAI->hasSingleParameterDotFile()) {
466  // .file "foo.c"
467 
468  SmallString<128> FileName;
469  if (MAI->hasBasenameOnlyForFileDirective())
470  FileName = llvm::sys::path::filename(M.getSourceFileName());
471  else
472  FileName = M.getSourceFileName();
473  if (MAI->hasFourStringsDotFile()) {
474 #ifdef PACKAGE_VENDOR
475  const char VerStr[] =
476  PACKAGE_VENDOR " " PACKAGE_NAME " version " PACKAGE_VERSION;
477 #else
478  const char VerStr[] = PACKAGE_NAME " version " PACKAGE_VERSION;
479 #endif
480  // TODO: Add timestamp and description.
481  OutStreamer->emitFileDirective(FileName, VerStr, "", "");
482  } else {
483  OutStreamer->emitFileDirective(FileName);
484  }
485  }
486 
487  GCModuleInfo *MI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<GCModuleInfo>();
488  assert(MI && "AsmPrinter didn't require GCModuleInfo?");
489  for (const auto &I : *MI)
490  if (GCMetadataPrinter *MP = getOrCreateGCPrinter(*I))
491  MP->beginAssembly(M, *MI, *this);
492 
493  // Emit module-level inline asm if it exists.
494  if (!M.getModuleInlineAsm().empty()) {
495  OutStreamer->AddComment("Start of file scope inline assembly");
496  OutStreamer->addBlankLine();
497  emitInlineAsm(M.getModuleInlineAsm() + "\n", *TM.getMCSubtargetInfo(),
498  TM.Options.MCOptions);
499  OutStreamer->AddComment("End of file scope inline assembly");
500  OutStreamer->addBlankLine();
501  }
502 
503  if (MAI->doesSupportDebugInformation()) {
504  bool EmitCodeView = M.getCodeViewFlag();
505  if (EmitCodeView && TM.getTargetTriple().isOSWindows()) {
506  Handlers.emplace_back(std::make_unique<CodeViewDebug>(this),
507  DbgTimerName, DbgTimerDescription,
508  CodeViewLineTablesGroupName,
509  CodeViewLineTablesGroupDescription);
510  }
511  if (!EmitCodeView || M.getDwarfVersion()) {
512  if (MMI->hasDebugInfo()) {
513  DD = new DwarfDebug(this);
514  Handlers.emplace_back(std::unique_ptr<DwarfDebug>(DD), DbgTimerName,
515  DbgTimerDescription, DWARFGroupName,
516  DWARFGroupDescription);
517  }
518  }
519  }
520 
521  if (M.getNamedMetadata(PseudoProbeDescMetadataName)) {
522  PP = new PseudoProbeHandler(this);
523  Handlers.emplace_back(std::unique_ptr<PseudoProbeHandler>(PP), PPTimerName,
524  PPTimerDescription, PPGroupName, PPGroupDescription);
525  }
526 
527  switch (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType()) {
528  case ExceptionHandling::None:
529  // We may want to emit CFI for debug.
530  [[fallthrough]];
531  case ExceptionHandling::SjLj:
532  case ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI:
533  case ExceptionHandling::ARM:
534  for (auto &F : M.getFunctionList()) {
535  if (getFunctionCFISectionType(F) != CFISection::None)
536  ModuleCFISection = getFunctionCFISectionType(F);
537  // If any function needsUnwindTableEntry(), it needs .eh_frame and hence
538  // the module needs .eh_frame. If we have found that case, we are done.
539  if (ModuleCFISection == CFISection::EH)
540  break;
541  }
542  assert(MAI->getExceptionHandlingType() == ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI ||
543  ModuleCFISection != CFISection::EH);
544  break;
545  default:
546  break;
547  }
548 
549  EHStreamer *ES = nullptr;
550  switch (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType()) {
551  case ExceptionHandling::None:
552  if (!needsCFIForDebug())
553  break;
554  [[fallthrough]];
555  case ExceptionHandling::SjLj:
556  case ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI:
557  ES = new DwarfCFIException(this);
558  break;
559  case ExceptionHandling::ARM:
560  ES = new ARMException(this);
561  break;
562  case ExceptionHandling::WinEH:
563  switch (MAI->getWinEHEncodingType()) {
564  default: llvm_unreachable("unsupported unwinding information encoding");
565  case WinEH::EncodingType::Invalid:
566  break;
567  case WinEH::EncodingType::X86:
568  case WinEH::EncodingType::Itanium:
569  ES = new WinException(this);
570  break;
571  }
572  break;
573  case ExceptionHandling::Wasm:
574  ES = new WasmException(this);
575  break;
576  case ExceptionHandling::AIX:
577  ES = new AIXException(this);
578  break;
579  }
580  if (ES)
581  Handlers.emplace_back(std::unique_ptr<EHStreamer>(ES), EHTimerName,
582  EHTimerDescription, DWARFGroupName,
583  DWARFGroupDescription);
584 
585  // Emit tables for any value of cfguard flag (i.e. cfguard=1 or cfguard=2).
586  if (mdconst::extract_or_null<ConstantInt>(M.getModuleFlag("cfguard")))
587  Handlers.emplace_back(std::make_unique<WinCFGuard>(this), CFGuardName,
588  CFGuardDescription, DWARFGroupName,
589  DWARFGroupDescription);
590 
591  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
592  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
593  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
594  HI.Handler->beginModule(&M);
595  }
596 
597  if (!BasicBlockProfileDump.empty()) {
598  std::error_code PossibleFileError;
599  MBBProfileDumpFileOutput = std::make_unique<raw_fd_ostream>(
600  BasicBlockProfileDump, PossibleFileError);
601  if (PossibleFileError) {
602  M.getContext().emitError("Failed to open file for MBB Profile Dump: " +
603  PossibleFileError.message() + "\n");
604  }
605  }
606 
607  return false;
608 }
609 
610 static bool canBeHidden(const GlobalValue *GV, const MCAsmInfo &MAI) {
611  if (!MAI.hasWeakDefCanBeHiddenDirective())
612  return false;
613 
614  return GV->canBeOmittedFromSymbolTable();
615 }
616 
617 void AsmPrinter::emitLinkage(const GlobalValue *GV, MCSymbol *GVSym) const {
618  GlobalValue::LinkageTypes Linkage = GV->getLinkage();
619  switch (Linkage) {
620  case GlobalValue::CommonLinkage:
621  case GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage:
622  case GlobalValue::LinkOnceODRLinkage:
623  case GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage:
624  case GlobalValue::WeakODRLinkage:
625  if (MAI->hasWeakDefDirective()) {
626  // .globl _foo
627  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Global);
628 
629  if (!canBeHidden(GV, *MAI))
630  // .weak_definition _foo
631  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_WeakDefinition);
632  else
633  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_WeakDefAutoPrivate);
634  } else if (MAI->avoidWeakIfComdat() && GV->hasComdat()) {
635  // .globl _foo
636  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Global);
637  //NOTE: linkonce is handled by the section the symbol was assigned to.
638  } else {
639  // .weak _foo
640  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Weak);
641  }
642  return;
643  case GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage:
644  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Global);
645  return;
646  case GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage:
647  case GlobalValue::InternalLinkage:
648  return;
649  case GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage:
650  case GlobalValue::AvailableExternallyLinkage:
651  case GlobalValue::AppendingLinkage:
652  llvm_unreachable("Should never emit this");
653  }
654  llvm_unreachable("Unknown linkage type!");
655 }
656 
657 void AsmPrinter::getNameWithPrefix(SmallVectorImpl<char> &Name,
658  const GlobalValue *GV) const {
659  TM.getNameWithPrefix(Name, GV, getObjFileLowering().getMangler());
660 }

662 MCSymbol *AsmPrinter::getSymbol(const GlobalValue *GV) const {
663  return TM.getSymbol(GV);
664 }
665 
666 MCSymbol *AsmPrinter::getSymbolPreferLocal(const GlobalValue &GV) const {
667  // On ELF, use .Lfoo$local if GV is a non-interposable GlobalObject with an
668  // exact definion (intersection of GlobalValue::hasExactDefinition() and
669  // !isInterposable()). These linkages include: external, appending, internal,
670  // private. It may be profitable to use a local alias for external. The
671  // assembler would otherwise be conservative and assume a global default
672  // visibility symbol can be interposable, even if the code generator already
673  // assumed it.
674  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() && GV.canBenefitFromLocalAlias()) {
675  const Module &M = *GV.getParent();
676  if (TM.getRelocationModel() != Reloc::Static &&
677  M.getPIELevel() == PIELevel::Default && GV.isDSOLocal())
678  return getSymbolWithGlobalValueBase(&GV, "$local");
679  }
680  return TM.getSymbol(&GV);
681 }
682 
683 /// EmitGlobalVariable - Emit the specified global variable to the .s file.
684 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalVariable(const GlobalVariable *GV) {
685  bool IsEmuTLSVar = TM.useEmulatedTLS() && GV->isThreadLocal();
686  assert(!(IsEmuTLSVar && GV->hasCommonLinkage()) &&
687  "No emulated TLS variables in the common section");
688 
689  // Never emit TLS variable xyz in emulated TLS model.
690  // The initialization value is in __emutls_t.xyz instead of xyz.
691  if (IsEmuTLSVar)
692  return;
693 
694  if (GV->hasInitializer()) {
695  // Check to see if this is a special global used by LLVM, if so, emit it.
696  if (emitSpecialLLVMGlobal(GV))
697  return;
698 
699  // Skip the emission of global equivalents. The symbol can be emitted later
700  // on by emitGlobalGOTEquivs in case it turns out to be needed.
701  if (GlobalGOTEquivs.count(getSymbol(GV)))
702  return;
703 
704  if (isVerbose()) {
705  // When printing the control variable __emutls_v.*,
706  // we don't need to print the original TLS variable name.
707  GV->printAsOperand(OutStreamer->getCommentOS(),
708  /*PrintType=*/false, GV->getParent());
709  OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << '\n';
710  }
711  }
712 
713  MCSymbol *GVSym = getSymbol(GV);
714  MCSymbol *EmittedSym = GVSym;
715 
716  // getOrCreateEmuTLSControlSym only creates the symbol with name and default
717  // attributes.
718  // GV's or GVSym's attributes will be used for the EmittedSym.
719  emitVisibility(EmittedSym, GV->getVisibility(), !GV->isDeclaration());
720 
721  if (GV->isTagged()) {
722  Triple T = TM.getTargetTriple();
723 
724  if (T.getArch() != Triple::aarch64 || !T.isAndroid())
725  OutContext.reportError(SMLoc(),
726  "Tagged symbols (-fsanitize=memtag-globals) are "
727  "only supported on aarch64 + Android.");
728  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(EmittedSym, MAI->getMemtagAttr());
729  }
730 
731  if (!GV->hasInitializer()) // External globals require no extra code.
732  return;
733 
734  GVSym->redefineIfPossible();
735  if (GVSym->isDefined() || GVSym->isVariable())
736  OutContext.reportError(SMLoc(), "symbol '" + Twine(GVSym->getName()) +
737  "' is already defined");
738 
739  if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective())
740  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(EmittedSym, MCSA_ELF_TypeObject);
741 
742  SectionKind GVKind = TargetLoweringObjectFile::getKindForGlobal(GV, TM);
743 
744  const DataLayout &DL = GV->getParent()->getDataLayout();
745  uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GV->getValueType());
746 
747  // If the alignment is specified, we *must* obey it. Overaligning a global
748  // with a specified alignment is a prompt way to break globals emitted to
749  // sections and expected to be contiguous (e.g. ObjC metadata).
750  const Align Alignment = getGVAlignment(GV, DL);
751 
752  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
753  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription,
754  HI.TimerGroupName, HI.TimerGroupDescription,
755  TimePassesIsEnabled);
756  HI.Handler->setSymbolSize(GVSym, Size);
757  }
758 
759  // Handle common symbols
760  if (GVKind.isCommon()) {
761  if (Size == 0) Size = 1; // .comm Foo, 0 is undefined, avoid it.
762  // .comm _foo, 42, 4
763  OutStreamer->emitCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Alignment);
764  return;
765  }
766 
767  // Determine to which section this global should be emitted.
768  MCSection *TheSection = getObjFileLowering().SectionForGlobal(GV, GVKind, TM);
769 
770  // If we have a bss global going to a section that supports the
771  // zerofill directive, do so here.
772  if (GVKind.isBSS() && MAI->hasMachoZeroFillDirective() &&
773  TheSection->isVirtualSection()) {
774  if (Size == 0)
775  Size = 1; // zerofill of 0 bytes is undefined.
776  emitLinkage(GV, GVSym);
777  // .zerofill __DATA, __bss, _foo, 400, 5
778  OutStreamer->emitZerofill(TheSection, GVSym, Size, Alignment);
779  return;
780  }
781 
782  // If this is a BSS local symbol and we are emitting in the BSS
783  // section use .lcomm/.comm directive.
784  if (GVKind.isBSSLocal() &&
785  getObjFileLowering().getBSSSection() == TheSection) {
786  if (Size == 0)
787  Size = 1; // .comm Foo, 0 is undefined, avoid it.
788 
789  // Use .lcomm only if it supports user-specified alignment.
790  // Otherwise, while it would still be correct to use .lcomm in some
791  // cases (e.g. when Align == 1), the external assembler might enfore
792  // some -unknown- default alignment behavior, which could cause
793  // spurious differences between external and integrated assembler.
794  // Prefer to simply fall back to .local / .comm in this case.
795  if (MAI->getLCOMMDirectiveAlignmentType() != LCOMM::NoAlignment) {
796  // .lcomm _foo, 42
797  OutStreamer->emitLocalCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Alignment);
798  return;
799  }
800 
801  // .local _foo
802  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(GVSym, MCSA_Local);
803  // .comm _foo, 42, 4
804  OutStreamer->emitCommonSymbol(GVSym, Size, Alignment);
805  return;
806  }
807 
808  // Handle thread local data for mach-o which requires us to output an
809  // additional structure of data and mangle the original symbol so that we
810  // can reference it later.
811  //
812  // TODO: This should become an "emit thread local global" method on TLOF.
813  // All of this macho specific stuff should be sunk down into TLOFMachO and
814  // stuff like "TLSExtraDataSection" should no longer be part of the parent
815  // TLOF class. This will also make it more obvious that stuff like
816  // MCStreamer::EmitTBSSSymbol is macho specific and only called from macho
817  // specific code.
818  if (GVKind.isThreadLocal() && MAI->hasMachoTBSSDirective()) {
819  // Emit the .tbss symbol
820  MCSymbol *MangSym =
821  OutContext.getOrCreateSymbol(GVSym->getName() + Twine("$tlv$init"));
822 
823  if (GVKind.isThreadBSS()) {
824  TheSection = getObjFileLowering().getTLSBSSSection();
825  OutStreamer->emitTBSSSymbol(TheSection, MangSym, Size, Alignment);
826  } else if (GVKind.isThreadData()) {
827  OutStreamer->switchSection(TheSection);
828 
829  emitAlignment(Alignment, GV);
830  OutStreamer->emitLabel(MangSym);
831 
832  emitGlobalConstant(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(),
833  GV->getInitializer());
834  }
835 
836  OutStreamer->addBlankLine();
837 
838  // Emit the variable struct for the runtime.
839  MCSection *TLVSect = getObjFileLowering().getTLSExtraDataSection();
840 
841  OutStreamer->switchSection(TLVSect);
842  // Emit the linkage here.
843  emitLinkage(GV, GVSym);
844  OutStreamer->emitLabel(GVSym);
845 
846  // Three pointers in size:
847  // - __tlv_bootstrap - used to make sure support exists
848  // - spare pointer, used when mapped by the runtime
849  // - pointer to mangled symbol above with initializer
850  unsigned PtrSize = DL.getPointerTypeSize(GV->getType());
851  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(GetExternalSymbolSymbol("_tlv_bootstrap"),
852  PtrSize);
853  OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, PtrSize);
854  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(MangSym, PtrSize);
855 
856  OutStreamer->addBlankLine();
857  return;
858  }
859 
860  MCSymbol *EmittedInitSym = GVSym;
861 
862  OutStreamer->switchSection(TheSection);
863 
864  emitLinkage(GV, EmittedInitSym);
865  emitAlignment(Alignment, GV);
866 
867  OutStreamer->emitLabel(EmittedInitSym);
868  MCSymbol *LocalAlias = getSymbolPreferLocal(*GV);
869  if (LocalAlias != EmittedInitSym)
870  OutStreamer->emitLabel(LocalAlias);
871 
872  emitGlobalConstant(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer());
873 
874  if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective())
875  // .size foo, 42
876  OutStreamer->emitELFSize(EmittedInitSym,
877  MCConstantExpr::create(Size, OutContext));
878 
879  OutStreamer->addBlankLine();
880 }

882 /// Emit the directive and value for debug thread local expression
883 ///
884 /// \p Value - The value to emit.
885 /// \p Size - The size of the integer (in bytes) to emit.
886 void AsmPrinter::emitDebugValue(const MCExpr *Value, unsigned Size) const {
887  OutStreamer->emitValue(Value, Size);
888 }

890 void AsmPrinter::emitFunctionHeaderComment() {}
891 
892 /// EmitFunctionHeader - This method emits the header for the current
893 /// function.
894 void AsmPrinter::emitFunctionHeader() {
895  const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
896 
897  if (isVerbose())
898  OutStreamer->getCommentOS()
899  << "-- Begin function "
900  << GlobalValue::dropLLVMManglingEscape(F.getName()) << '\n';
901 
902  // Print out constants referenced by the function
903  emitConstantPool();
904 
905  // Print the 'header' of function.
906  // If basic block sections are desired, explicitly request a unique section
907  // for this function's entry block.
908  if (MF->front().isBeginSection())
909  MF->setSection(getObjFileLowering().getUniqueSectionForFunction(F, TM));
910  else
911  MF->setSection(getObjFileLowering().SectionForGlobal(&F, TM));
912  OutStreamer->switchSection(MF->getSection());
913 
914  if (!MAI->hasVisibilityOnlyWithLinkage())
915  emitVisibility(CurrentFnSym, F.getVisibility());
916 
917  if (MAI->needsFunctionDescriptors())
918  emitLinkage(&F, CurrentFnDescSym);
919 
920  emitLinkage(&F, CurrentFnSym);
921  if (MAI->hasFunctionAlignment())
922  emitAlignment(MF->getAlignment(), &F);
923 
924  if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective())
925  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(CurrentFnSym, MCSA_ELF_TypeFunction);
926 
927  if (F.hasFnAttribute(Attribute::Cold))
928  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(CurrentFnSym, MCSA_Cold);
929 
930  if (isVerbose()) {
931  F.printAsOperand(OutStreamer->getCommentOS(),
932  /*PrintType=*/false, F.getParent());
933  emitFunctionHeaderComment();
934  OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << '\n';
935  }
936 
937  // Emit the prefix data.
938  if (F.hasPrefixData()) {
939  if (MAI->hasSubsectionsViaSymbols()) {
940  // Preserving prefix data on platforms which use subsections-via-symbols
941  // is a bit tricky. Here we introduce a symbol for the prefix data
942  // and use the .alt_entry attribute to mark the function's real entry point
943  // as an alternative entry point to the prefix-data symbol.
944  MCSymbol *PrefixSym = OutContext.createLinkerPrivateTempSymbol();
945  OutStreamer->emitLabel(PrefixSym);
946 
947  emitGlobalConstant(F.getParent()->getDataLayout(), F.getPrefixData());
948 
949  // Emit an .alt_entry directive for the actual function symbol.
950  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(CurrentFnSym, MCSA_AltEntry);
951  } else {
952  emitGlobalConstant(F.getParent()->getDataLayout(), F.getPrefixData());
953  }
954  }
955 
956  // Emit KCFI type information before patchable-function-prefix nops.
957  emitKCFITypeId(*MF);
958 
959  // Emit M NOPs for -fpatchable-function-entry=N,M where M>0. We arbitrarily
960  // place prefix data before NOPs.
961  unsigned PatchableFunctionPrefix = 0;
962  unsigned PatchableFunctionEntry = 0;
963  (void)F.getFnAttribute("patchable-function-prefix")
964  .getValueAsString()
965  .getAsInteger(10, PatchableFunctionPrefix);
966  (void)F.getFnAttribute("patchable-function-entry")
967  .getValueAsString()
968  .getAsInteger(10, PatchableFunctionEntry);
969  if (PatchableFunctionPrefix) {
970  CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym =
971  OutContext.createLinkerPrivateTempSymbol();
972  OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym);
973  emitNops(PatchableFunctionPrefix);
974  } else if (PatchableFunctionEntry) {
975  // May be reassigned when emitting the body, to reference the label after
976  // the initial BTI (AArch64) or endbr32/endbr64 (x86).
977  CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym = CurrentFnBegin;
978  }
979 
980  // Emit the function descriptor. This is a virtual function to allow targets
981  // to emit their specific function descriptor. Right now it is only used by
982  // the AIX target. The PowerPC 64-bit V1 ELF target also uses function
983  // descriptors and should be converted to use this hook as well.
984  if (MAI->needsFunctionDescriptors())
985  emitFunctionDescriptor();
986 
987  // Emit the CurrentFnSym. This is a virtual function to allow targets to do
988  // their wild and crazy things as required.
989  emitFunctionEntryLabel();
990 
991  // If the function had address-taken blocks that got deleted, then we have
992  // references to the dangling symbols. Emit them at the start of the function
993  // so that we don't get references to undefined symbols.
994  std::vector<MCSymbol*> DeadBlockSyms;
995  takeDeletedSymbolsForFunction(&F, DeadBlockSyms);
996  for (MCSymbol *DeadBlockSym : DeadBlockSyms) {
997  OutStreamer->AddComment("Address taken block that was later removed");
998  OutStreamer->emitLabel(DeadBlockSym);
999  }
1000 
1001  if (CurrentFnBegin) {
1002  if (MAI->useAssignmentForEHBegin()) {
1003  MCSymbol *CurPos = OutContext.createTempSymbol();
1004  OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurPos);
1005  OutStreamer->emitAssignment(CurrentFnBegin,
1006  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurPos, OutContext));
1007  } else {
1008  OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurrentFnBegin);
1009  }
1010  }
1011 
1012  // Emit pre-function debug and/or EH information.
1013  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1014  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1015  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1016  HI.Handler->beginFunction(MF);
1017  }
1018  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1019  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1020  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1021  HI.Handler->beginBasicBlockSection(MF->front());
1022  }
1023 
1024  // Emit the prologue data.
1025  if (F.hasPrologueData())
1026  emitGlobalConstant(F.getParent()->getDataLayout(), F.getPrologueData());
1027 
1028  // Emit the function prologue data for the indirect call sanitizer.
1029  if (const MDNode *MD = F.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_func_sanitize)) {
1030  assert(TM.getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::x86 ||
1031  TM.getTargetTriple().getArch() == Triple::x86_64);
1032  assert(MD->getNumOperands() == 2);
1033 
1034  auto *PrologueSig = mdconst::extract<Constant>(MD->getOperand(0));
1035  auto *FTRTTIProxy = mdconst::extract<Constant>(MD->getOperand(1));
1036  assert(PrologueSig && FTRTTIProxy);
1037  emitGlobalConstant(F.getParent()->getDataLayout(), PrologueSig);
1038 
1039  const MCExpr *Proxy = lowerConstant(FTRTTIProxy);
1040  const MCExpr *FnExp = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentFnSym, OutContext);
1041  const MCExpr *PCRel = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Proxy, FnExp, OutContext);
1042  // Use 32 bit since only small code model is supported.
1043  OutStreamer->emitValue(PCRel, 4u);
1044  }
1045 }
1046 
1047 /// EmitFunctionEntryLabel - Emit the label that is the entrypoint for the
1048 /// function. This can be overridden by targets as required to do custom stuff.
1049 void AsmPrinter::emitFunctionEntryLabel() {
1050  CurrentFnSym->redefineIfPossible();
1051 
1052  // The function label could have already been emitted if two symbols end up
1053  // conflicting due to asm renaming. Detect this and emit an error.
1054  if (CurrentFnSym->isVariable())
1055  report_fatal_error("'" + Twine(CurrentFnSym->getName()) +
1056  "' is a protected alias");
1057 
1058  OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurrentFnSym);
1059 
1060  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
1061  MCSymbol *Sym = getSymbolPreferLocal(MF->getFunction());
1062  if (Sym != CurrentFnSym) {
1063  cast<MCSymbolELF>(Sym)->setType(ELF::STT_FUNC);
1064  CurrentFnBeginLocal = Sym;
1065  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Sym);
1066  if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective())
1067  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, MCSA_ELF_TypeFunction);
1068  }
1069  }
1070 }
1071 
1072 /// emitComments - Pretty-print comments for instructions.
1073 static void emitComments(const MachineInstr &MI, raw_ostream &CommentOS) {
1074  const MachineFunction *MF = MI.getMF();
1075  const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
1076 
1077  // Check for spills and reloads
1078 
1079  // We assume a single instruction only has a spill or reload, not
1080  // both.
1081  std::optional<unsigned> Size;
1082  if ((Size = MI.getRestoreSize(TII))) {
1083  CommentOS << *Size << "-byte Reload\n";
1084  } else if ((Size = MI.getFoldedRestoreSize(TII))) {
1085  if (*Size) {
1086  if (*Size == unsigned(MemoryLocation::UnknownSize))
1087  CommentOS << "Unknown-size Folded Reload\n";
1088  else
1089  CommentOS << *Size << "-byte Folded Reload\n";
1090  }
1091  } else if ((Size = MI.getSpillSize(TII))) {
1092  CommentOS << *Size << "-byte Spill\n";
1093  } else if ((Size = MI.getFoldedSpillSize(TII))) {
1094  if (*Size) {
1095  if (*Size == unsigned(MemoryLocation::UnknownSize))
1096  CommentOS << "Unknown-size Folded Spill\n";
1097  else
1098  CommentOS << *Size << "-byte Folded Spill\n";
1099  }
1100  }
1101 
1102  // Check for spill-induced copies
1103  if (MI.getAsmPrinterFlag(MachineInstr::ReloadReuse))
1104  CommentOS << " Reload Reuse\n";
1105 }
1106 
1107 /// emitImplicitDef - This method emits the specified machine instruction
1108 /// that is an implicit def.
1109 void AsmPrinter::emitImplicitDef(const MachineInstr *MI) const {
1110  Register RegNo = MI->getOperand(0).getReg();
1111 
1112  SmallString<128> Str;
1113  raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
1114  OS << "implicit-def: "
1115  << printReg(RegNo, MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo());
1116 
1117  OutStreamer->AddComment(OS.str());
1118  OutStreamer->addBlankLine();
1119 }
1120 
1121 static void emitKill(const MachineInstr *MI, AsmPrinter &AP) {
1122  std::string Str;
1123  raw_string_ostream OS(Str);
1124  OS << "kill:";
1125  for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->operands()) {
1126  assert(Op.isReg() && "KILL instruction must have only register operands");
1127  OS << ' ' << (Op.isDef() ? "def " : "killed ")
1128  << printReg(Op.getReg(), AP.MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo());
1129  }
1130  AP.OutStreamer->AddComment(OS.str());
1131  AP.OutStreamer->addBlankLine();
1132 }
1133 
1134 /// emitDebugValueComment - This method handles the target-independent form
1135 /// of DBG_VALUE, returning true if it was able to do so. A false return
1136 /// means the target will need to handle MI in EmitInstruction.
1137 static bool emitDebugValueComment(const MachineInstr *MI, AsmPrinter &AP) {
1138  // This code handles only the 4-operand target-independent form.
1139  if (MI->isNonListDebugValue() && MI->getNumOperands() != 4)
1140  return false;
1141 
1142  SmallString<128> Str;
1143  raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
1144  OS << "DEBUG_VALUE: ";
1145 
1146  const DILocalVariable *V = MI->getDebugVariable();
1147  if (auto *SP = dyn_cast<DISubprogram>(V->getScope())) {
1148  StringRef Name = SP->getName();
1149  if (!Name.empty())
1150  OS << Name << ":";
1151  }
1152  OS << V->getName();
1153  OS << " <- ";
1154 
1155  const DIExpression *Expr = MI->getDebugExpression();
1156  // First convert this to a non-variadic expression if possible, to simplify
1157  // the output.
1158  if (auto NonVariadicExpr = DIExpression::convertToNonVariadicExpression(Expr))
1159  Expr = *NonVariadicExpr;
1160  // Then, output the possibly-simplified expression.
1161  if (Expr->getNumElements()) {
1162  OS << '[';
1163  ListSeparator LS;
1164  for (auto &Op : Expr->expr_ops()) {
1165  OS << LS << dwarf::OperationEncodingString(Op.getOp());
1166  for (unsigned I = 0; I < Op.getNumArgs(); ++I)
1167  OS << ' ' << Op.getArg(I);
1168  }
1169  OS << "] ";
1170  }
1171 
1172  // Register or immediate value. Register 0 means undef.
1173  for (const MachineOperand &Op : MI->debug_operands()) {
1174  if (&Op != MI->debug_operands().begin())
1175  OS << ", ";
1176  switch (Op.getType()) {
1177  case MachineOperand::MO_FPImmediate: {
1178  APFloat APF = APFloat(Op.getFPImm()->getValueAPF());
1179  Type *ImmTy = Op.getFPImm()->getType();
1180  if (ImmTy->isBFloatTy() || ImmTy->isHalfTy() || ImmTy->isFloatTy() ||
1181  ImmTy->isDoubleTy()) {
1182  OS << APF.convertToDouble();
1183  } else {
1184  // There is no good way to print long double. Convert a copy to
1185  // double. Ah well, it's only a comment.
1186  bool ignored;
1187  APF.convert(APFloat::IEEEdouble(), APFloat::rmNearestTiesToEven,
1188  &ignored);
1189  OS << "(long double) " << APF.convertToDouble();
1190  }
1191  break;
1192  }
1193  case MachineOperand::MO_Immediate: {
1194  OS << Op.getImm();
1195  break;
1196  }
1197  case MachineOperand::MO_CImmediate: {
1198  Op.getCImm()->getValue().print(OS, false /*isSigned*/);
1199  break;
1200  }
1201  case MachineOperand::MO_TargetIndex: {
1202  OS << "!target-index(" << Op.getIndex() << "," << Op.getOffset() << ")";
1203  break;
1204  }
1205  case MachineOperand::MO_Register:
1206  case MachineOperand::MO_FrameIndex: {
1207  Register Reg;
1208  std::optional<StackOffset> Offset;
1209  if (Op.isReg()) {
1210  Reg = Op.getReg();
1211  } else {
1212  const TargetFrameLowering *TFI =
1213  AP.MF->getSubtarget().getFrameLowering();
1214  Offset = TFI->getFrameIndexReference(*AP.MF, Op.getIndex(), Reg);
1215  }
1216  if (!Reg) {
1217  // Suppress offset, it is not meaningful here.
1218  OS << "undef";
1219  break;
1220  }
1221  // The second operand is only an offset if it's an immediate.
1222  if (MI->isIndirectDebugValue())
1223  Offset = StackOffset::getFixed(MI->getDebugOffset().getImm());
1224  if (Offset)
1225  OS << '[';
1226  OS << printReg(Reg, AP.MF->getSubtarget().getRegisterInfo());
1227  if (Offset)
1228  OS << '+' << Offset->getFixed() << ']';
1229  break;
1230  }
1231  default:
1232  llvm_unreachable("Unknown operand type");
1233  }
1234  }
1235 
1236  // NOTE: Want this comment at start of line, don't emit with AddComment.
1237  AP.OutStreamer->emitRawComment(OS.str());
1238  return true;
1239 }
1240 
1241 /// This method handles the target-independent form of DBG_LABEL, returning
1242 /// true if it was able to do so. A false return means the target will need
1243 /// to handle MI in EmitInstruction.
1244 static bool emitDebugLabelComment(const MachineInstr *MI, AsmPrinter &AP) {
1245  if (MI->getNumOperands() != 1)
1246  return false;
1247 
1248  SmallString<128> Str;
1249  raw_svector_ostream OS(Str);
1250  OS << "DEBUG_LABEL: ";
1251 
1252  const DILabel *V = MI->getDebugLabel();
1253  if (auto *SP = dyn_cast<DISubprogram>(
1254  V->getScope()->getNonLexicalBlockFileScope())) {
1255  StringRef Name = SP->getName();
1256  if (!Name.empty())
1257  OS << Name << ":";
1258  }
1259  OS << V->getName();
1260 
1261  // NOTE: Want this comment at start of line, don't emit with AddComment.
1262  AP.OutStreamer->emitRawComment(OS.str());
1263  return true;
1264 }

1266 AsmPrinter::CFISection
1267 AsmPrinter::getFunctionCFISectionType(const Function &F) const {
1268  // Ignore functions that won't get emitted.
1269  if (F.isDeclarationForLinker())
1270  return CFISection::None;
1271 
1272  if (MAI->getExceptionHandlingType() == ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI &&
1273  F.needsUnwindTableEntry())
1274  return CFISection::EH;
1275 
1276  if (MMI->hasDebugInfo() || TM.Options.ForceDwarfFrameSection)
1277  return CFISection::Debug;
1278 
1279  return CFISection::None;
1280 }
1281

1283 AsmPrinter::getFunctionCFISectionType(const MachineFunction &MF) const {
1284  return getFunctionCFISectionType(MF.getFunction());
1285 }

1288  return MAI->usesWindowsCFI() && MF->getFunction().needsUnwindTableEntry();
1289 }
1290 
1291 bool AsmPrinter::needsCFIForDebug() const {
1292  return MAI->getExceptionHandlingType() == ExceptionHandling::None &&
1293  MAI->doesUseCFIForDebug() && ModuleCFISection == CFISection::Debug;
1294 }
1295 
1296 void AsmPrinter::emitCFIInstruction(const MachineInstr &MI) {
1297  ExceptionHandling ExceptionHandlingType = MAI->getExceptionHandlingType();
1298  if (!needsCFIForDebug() &&
1299  ExceptionHandlingType != ExceptionHandling::DwarfCFI &&
1300  ExceptionHandlingType != ExceptionHandling::ARM)
1301  return;
1302 
1303  if (getFunctionCFISectionType(*MF) == CFISection::None)
1304  return;
1305 
1306  // If there is no "real" instruction following this CFI instruction, skip
1307  // emitting it; it would be beyond the end of the function's FDE range.
1308  auto *MBB = MI.getParent();
1309  auto I = std::next(MI.getIterator());
1310  while (I != MBB->end() && I->isTransient())
1311  ++I;
1312  if (I == MBB->instr_end() &&
1313  MBB->getReverseIterator() == MBB->getParent()->rbegin())
1314  return;
1315 
1316  const std::vector<MCCFIInstruction> &Instrs = MF->getFrameInstructions();
1317  unsigned CFIIndex = MI.getOperand(0).getCFIIndex();
1318  const MCCFIInstruction &CFI = Instrs[CFIIndex];
1319  emitCFIInstruction(CFI);
1320 }
1321 
1322 void AsmPrinter::emitFrameAlloc(const MachineInstr &MI) {
1323  // The operands are the MCSymbol and the frame offset of the allocation.
1324  MCSymbol *FrameAllocSym = MI.getOperand(0).getMCSymbol();
1325  int FrameOffset = MI.getOperand(1).getImm();
1326 
1327  // Emit a symbol assignment.
1328  OutStreamer->emitAssignment(FrameAllocSym,
1329  MCConstantExpr::create(FrameOffset, OutContext));
1330 }
1331 
1332 /// Returns the BB metadata to be emitted in the .llvm_bb_addr_map section for a
1333 /// given basic block. This can be used to capture more precise profile
1334 /// information. We use the last 4 bits (LSBs) to encode the following
1335 /// information:
1336 /// * (1): set if return block (ret or tail call).
1337 /// * (2): set if ends with a tail call.
1338 /// * (3): set if exception handling (EH) landing pad.
1339 /// * (4): set if the block can fall through to its next.
1340 /// The remaining bits are zero.
1341 static unsigned getBBAddrMapMetadata(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) {
1342  const TargetInstrInfo *TII = MBB.getParent()->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo();
1343  return ((unsigned)MBB.isReturnBlock()) |
1344  ((!MBB.empty() && TII->isTailCall(MBB.back())) << 1) |
1345  (MBB.isEHPad() << 2) |
1346  (const_cast<MachineBasicBlock &>(MBB).canFallThrough() << 3);
1347 }
1348 
1349 void AsmPrinter::emitBBAddrMapSection(const MachineFunction &MF) {
1350  MCSection *BBAddrMapSection =
1351  getObjFileLowering().getBBAddrMapSection(*MF.getSection());
1352  assert(BBAddrMapSection && ".llvm_bb_addr_map section is not initialized.");
1353 
1354  const MCSymbol *FunctionSymbol = getFunctionBegin();
1355 
1356  OutStreamer->pushSection();
1357  OutStreamer->switchSection(BBAddrMapSection);
1358  OutStreamer->AddComment("version");
1359  uint8_t BBAddrMapVersion = OutStreamer->getContext().getBBAddrMapVersion();
1360  OutStreamer->emitInt8(BBAddrMapVersion);
1361  OutStreamer->AddComment("feature");
1362  OutStreamer->emitInt8(0);
1363  OutStreamer->AddComment("function address");
1364  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(FunctionSymbol, getPointerSize());
1365  OutStreamer->AddComment("number of basic blocks");
1366  OutStreamer->emitULEB128IntValue(MF.size());
1367  const MCSymbol *PrevMBBEndSymbol = FunctionSymbol;
1368  // Emit BB Information for each basic block in the funciton.
1369  for (const MachineBasicBlock &MBB : MF) {
1370  const MCSymbol *MBBSymbol =
1371  MBB.isEntryBlock() ? FunctionSymbol : MBB.getSymbol();
1372  // TODO: Remove this check when version 1 is deprecated.
1373  if (BBAddrMapVersion > 1) {
1374  OutStreamer->AddComment("BB id");
1375  // Emit the BB ID for this basic block.
1376  OutStreamer->emitULEB128IntValue(*MBB.getBBID());
1377  }
1378  // Emit the basic block offset relative to the end of the previous block.
1379  // This is zero unless the block is padded due to alignment.
1380  emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(MBBSymbol, PrevMBBEndSymbol);
1381  // Emit the basic block size. When BBs have alignments, their size cannot
1382  // always be computed from their offsets.
1383  emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(MBB.getEndSymbol(), MBBSymbol);
1384  // Emit the Metadata.
1385  OutStreamer->emitULEB128IntValue(getBBAddrMapMetadata(MBB));
1386  PrevMBBEndSymbol = MBB.getEndSymbol();
1387  }
1388  OutStreamer->popSection();
1389 }
1390 
1391 void AsmPrinter::emitKCFITrapEntry(const MachineFunction &MF,
1392  const MCSymbol *Symbol) {
1393  MCSection *Section =
1394  getObjFileLowering().getKCFITrapSection(*MF.getSection());
1395  if (!Section)
1396  return;
1397 
1398  OutStreamer->pushSection();
1399  OutStreamer->switchSection(Section);
1400 
1401  MCSymbol *Loc = OutContext.createLinkerPrivateTempSymbol();
1402  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Loc);
1403  OutStreamer->emitAbsoluteSymbolDiff(Symbol, Loc, 4);
1404 
1405  OutStreamer->popSection();
1406 }

1426 void AsmPrinter::emitStackSizeSection(const MachineFunction &MF) {
1427  if (!MF.getTarget().Options.EmitStackSizeSection)
1428  return;
1429 
1430  MCSection *StackSizeSection =
1431  getObjFileLowering().getStackSizesSection(*getCurrentSection());
1432  if (!StackSizeSection)
1433  return;
1434 
1435  const MachineFrameInfo &FrameInfo = MF.getFrameInfo();
1436  // Don't emit functions with dynamic stack allocations.
1437  if (FrameInfo.hasVarSizedObjects())
1438  return;
1439 
1440  OutStreamer->pushSection();
1441  OutStreamer->switchSection(StackSizeSection);
1442 
1443  const MCSymbol *FunctionSymbol = getFunctionBegin();
1444  uint64_t StackSize =
1445  FrameInfo.getStackSize() + FrameInfo.getUnsafeStackSize();
1446  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(FunctionSymbol, TM.getProgramPointerSize());
1447  OutStreamer->emitULEB128IntValue(StackSize);
1448 
1449  OutStreamer->popSection();
1450 }

1452 void AsmPrinter::emitStackUsage(const MachineFunction &MF) {
1453  const std::string &OutputFilename = MF.getTarget().Options.StackUsageOutput;
1454 
1455  // OutputFilename empty implies -fstack-usage is not passed.
1456  if (OutputFilename.empty())
1457  return;
1458 
1459  const MachineFrameInfo &FrameInfo = MF.getFrameInfo();
1460  uint64_t StackSize =
1461  FrameInfo.getStackSize() + FrameInfo.getUnsafeStackSize();
1462 
1463  if (StackUsageStream == nullptr) {
1464  std::error_code EC;
1465  StackUsageStream =
1466  std::make_unique<raw_fd_ostream>(OutputFilename, EC, sys::fs::OF_Text);
1467  if (EC) {
1468  errs() << "Could not open file: " << EC.message();
1469  return;
1470  }
1471  }
1472 
1473  *StackUsageStream << MF.getFunction().getParent()->getName();
1474  if (const DISubprogram *DSP = MF.getFunction().getSubprogram())
1475  *StackUsageStream << ':' << DSP->getLine();
1476 
1477  *StackUsageStream << ':' << MF.getName() << '\t' << StackSize << '\t';
1478  if (FrameInfo.hasVarSizedObjects())
1479  *StackUsageStream << "dynamic\n";
1480  else
1481  *StackUsageStream << "static\n";
1482 }

1484 void AsmPrinter::emitPCSectionsLabel(const MachineFunction &MF,
1485  const MDNode &MD) {
1486  MCSymbol *S = MF.getContext().createTempSymbol("pcsection");

1488  PCSectionsSymbols[&MD].emplace_back(S);
1489 }
1490 
1491 void AsmPrinter::emitPCSections(const MachineFunction &MF) {
1492  const Function &F = MF.getFunction();
1493  if (PCSectionsSymbols.empty() && !F.hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_pcsections))
1494  return;
1495 
1496  const CodeModel::Model CM = MF.getTarget().getCodeModel();
1497  const unsigned RelativeRelocSize =
1498  (CM == CodeModel::Medium || CM == CodeModel::Large) ? getPointerSize()
1499  : 4;
1500 
1501  // Switch to PCSection, short-circuiting the common case where the current
1502  // section is still valid (assume most MD_pcsections contain just 1 section).
1503  auto SwitchSection = [&, Prev = StringRef()](const StringRef &Sec) mutable {
1504  if (Sec == Prev)
1505  return;
1506  MCSection *S = getObjFileLowering().getPCSection(Sec, MF.getSection());
1507  assert(S && "PC section is not initialized");
1508  OutStreamer->switchSection(S);
1509  Prev = Sec;
1510  };
1511  // Emit symbols into sections and data as specified in the pcsections MDNode.
1512  auto EmitForMD = [&](const MDNode &MD, ArrayRef<const MCSymbol *> Syms,
1513  bool Deltas) {
1514  // Expect the first operand to be a section name. After that, a tuple of
1515  // constants may appear, which will simply be emitted into the current
1516  // section (the user of MD_pcsections decides the format of encoded data).
1517  assert(isa<MDString>(MD.getOperand(0)) && "first operand not a string");
1518  bool ConstULEB128 = false;
1519  for (const MDOperand &MDO : MD.operands()) {
1520  if (auto *S = dyn_cast<MDString>(MDO)) {
1521  // Found string, start of new section!
1522  // Find options for this section "<section>!<opts>" - supported options:
1523  // C = Compress constant integers of size 2-8 bytes as ULEB128.
1524  const StringRef SecWithOpt = S->getString();
1525  const size_t OptStart = SecWithOpt.find('!'); // likely npos
1526  const StringRef Sec = SecWithOpt.substr(0, OptStart);
1527  const StringRef Opts = SecWithOpt.substr(OptStart); // likely empty
1528  ConstULEB128 = Opts.find('C') != StringRef::npos;
1529 #ifndef NDEBUG
1530  for (char O : Opts)
1531  assert((O == '!' || O == 'C') && "Invalid !pcsections options");
1532 #endif
1533  SwitchSection(Sec);
1534  const MCSymbol *Prev = Syms.front();
1535  for (const MCSymbol *Sym : Syms) {
1536  if (Sym == Prev || !Deltas) {
1537  // Use the entry itself as the base of the relative offset.
1538  MCSymbol *Base = MF.getContext().createTempSymbol("pcsection_base");
1539  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Base);
1540  // Emit relative relocation `addr - base`, which avoids a dynamic
1541  // relocation in the final binary. User will get the address with
1542  // `base + addr`.
1543  emitLabelDifference(Sym, Base, RelativeRelocSize);
1544  } else {
1545  // Emit delta between symbol and previous symbol.
1546  if (ConstULEB128)
1547  emitLabelDifferenceAsULEB128(Sym, Prev);
1548  else
1549  emitLabelDifference(Sym, Prev, 4);
1550  }
1551  Prev = Sym;
1552  }
1553  } else {
1554  // Emit auxiliary data after PC.
1555  assert(isa<MDNode>(MDO) && "expecting either string or tuple");
1556  const auto *AuxMDs = cast<MDNode>(MDO);
1557  for (const MDOperand &AuxMDO : AuxMDs->operands()) {
1558  assert(isa<ConstantAsMetadata>(AuxMDO) && "expecting a constant");
1559  const Constant *C = cast<ConstantAsMetadata>(AuxMDO)->getValue();
1560  const DataLayout &DL = F.getParent()->getDataLayout();
1561  const uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeStoreSize(C->getType());
1562 
1563  if (auto *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(C);
1564  CI && ConstULEB128 && Size > 1 && Size <= 8) {
1565  emitULEB128(CI->getZExtValue());
1566  } else {
1567  emitGlobalConstant(DL, C);
1568  }
1569  }
1570  }
1571  }
1572  };
1573 
1574  OutStreamer->pushSection();
1575  // Emit PCs for function start and function size.
1576  if (const MDNode *MD = F.getMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_pcsections))
1577  EmitForMD(*MD, {getFunctionBegin(), getFunctionEnd()}, true);
1578  // Emit PCs for instructions collected.
1579  for (const auto &MS : PCSectionsSymbols)
1580  EmitForMD(*MS.first, MS.second, false);
1581  OutStreamer->popSection();
1582  PCSectionsSymbols.clear();
1583 }
1584 
1585 /// Returns true if function begin and end labels should be emitted.
1586 static bool needFuncLabels(const MachineFunction &MF) {
1587  MachineModuleInfo &MMI = MF.getMMI();
1588  if (!MF.getLandingPads().empty() || MF.hasEHFunclets() ||
1589  MMI.hasDebugInfo() ||
1590  MF.getFunction().hasMetadata(LLVMContext::MD_pcsections))
1591  return true;
1592 
1593  // We might emit an EH table that uses function begin and end labels even if
1594  // we don't have any landingpads.
1595  if (!MF.getFunction().hasPersonalityFn())
1596  return false;
1597  return !isNoOpWithoutInvoke(
1598  classifyEHPersonality(MF.getFunction().getPersonalityFn()));
1599 }
1600 
1601 /// EmitFunctionBody - This method emits the body and trailer for a
1602 /// function.
1603 void AsmPrinter::emitFunctionBody() {
1604  emitFunctionHeader();
1605 
1606  // Emit target-specific gunk before the function body.
1607  emitFunctionBodyStart();
1608 
1609  if (isVerbose()) {
1610  // Get MachineDominatorTree or compute it on the fly if it's unavailable
1611  MDT = getAnalysisIfAvailable<MachineDominatorTree>();
1612  if (!MDT) {
1613  OwnedMDT = std::make_unique<MachineDominatorTree>();
1614  OwnedMDT->getBase().recalculate(*MF);
1615  MDT = OwnedMDT.get();
1616  }
1617 
1618  // Get MachineLoopInfo or compute it on the fly if it's unavailable
1619  MLI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<MachineLoopInfo>();
1620  if (!MLI) {
1621  OwnedMLI = std::make_unique<MachineLoopInfo>();
1622  OwnedMLI->getBase().analyze(MDT->getBase());
1623  MLI = OwnedMLI.get();
1624  }
1625  }
1626 
1627  // Print out code for the function.
1628  bool HasAnyRealCode = false;
1629  int NumInstsInFunction = 0;
1630 
1631  bool CanDoExtraAnalysis = ORE->allowExtraAnalysis(DEBUG_TYPE);
1632  for (auto &MBB : *MF) {
1633  // Print a label for the basic block.
1634  emitBasicBlockStart(MBB);
1635  DenseMap<StringRef, unsigned> MnemonicCounts;
1636  for (auto &MI : MBB) {
1637  // Print the assembly for the instruction.
1638  if (!MI.isPosition() && !MI.isImplicitDef() && !MI.isKill() &&
1639  !MI.isDebugInstr()) {
1640  HasAnyRealCode = true;
1641  ++NumInstsInFunction;
1642  }
1643 
1644  // If there is a pre-instruction symbol, emit a label for it here.
1645  if (MCSymbol *S = MI.getPreInstrSymbol())
1646  OutStreamer->emitLabel(S);
1647 
1648  if (MDNode *MD = MI.getPCSections())
1649  emitPCSectionsLabel(*MF, *MD);
1650 
1651  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1652  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1653  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1654  HI.Handler->beginInstruction(&MI);
1655  }
1656 
1657  if (isVerbose())
1658  emitComments(MI, OutStreamer->getCommentOS());
1659 
1660  switch (MI.getOpcode()) {
1661  case TargetOpcode::CFI_INSTRUCTION:
1662  emitCFIInstruction(MI);
1663  break;
1664  case TargetOpcode::LOCAL_ESCAPE:
1665  emitFrameAlloc(MI);
1666  break;
1667  case TargetOpcode::ANNOTATION_LABEL:
1668  case TargetOpcode::EH_LABEL:
1669  case TargetOpcode::GC_LABEL:
1670  OutStreamer->emitLabel(MI.getOperand(0).getMCSymbol());
1671  break;
1672  case TargetOpcode::INLINEASM:
1673  case TargetOpcode::INLINEASM_BR:
1674  emitInlineAsm(&MI);
1675  break;
1676  case TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE:
1677  case TargetOpcode::DBG_VALUE_LIST:
1678  if (isVerbose()) {
1679  if (!emitDebugValueComment(&MI, *this))
1680  emitInstruction(&MI);
1681  }
1682  break;
1683  case TargetOpcode::DBG_INSTR_REF:
1684  // This instruction reference will have been resolved to a machine
1685  // location, and a nearby DBG_VALUE created. We can safely ignore
1686  // the instruction reference.
1687  break;
1688  case TargetOpcode::DBG_PHI:
1689  // This instruction is only used to label a program point, it's purely
1690  // meta information.
1691  break;
1692  case TargetOpcode::DBG_LABEL:
1693  if (isVerbose()) {
1694  if (!emitDebugLabelComment(&MI, *this))
1695  emitInstruction(&MI);
1696  }
1697  break;
1698  case TargetOpcode::IMPLICIT_DEF:
1699  if (isVerbose()) emitImplicitDef(&MI);
1700  break;
1701  case TargetOpcode::KILL:
1702  if (isVerbose()) emitKill(&MI, *this);
1703  break;
1704  case TargetOpcode::PSEUDO_PROBE:
1705  emitPseudoProbe(MI);
1706  break;
1707  case TargetOpcode::ARITH_FENCE:
1708  if (isVerbose())
1709  OutStreamer->emitRawComment("ARITH_FENCE");
1710  break;
1711  case TargetOpcode::MEMBARRIER:
1712  OutStreamer->emitRawComment("MEMBARRIER");
1713  break;
1714  default:
1715  emitInstruction(&MI);
1716  if (CanDoExtraAnalysis) {
1717  MCInst MCI;
1718  MCI.setOpcode(MI.getOpcode());
1719  auto Name = OutStreamer->getMnemonic(MCI);
1720  auto I = MnemonicCounts.insert({Name, 0u});
1721  I.first->second++;
1722  }
1723  break;
1724  }
1725 
1726  // If there is a post-instruction symbol, emit a label for it here.
1727  if (MCSymbol *S = MI.getPostInstrSymbol())
1728  OutStreamer->emitLabel(S);
1729 
1730  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1731  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1732  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1733  HI.Handler->endInstruction();
1734  }
1735  }
1736 
1737  // We must emit temporary symbol for the end of this basic block, if either
1738  // we have BBLabels enabled or if this basic blocks marks the end of a
1739  // section.
1740  if (MF->hasBBLabels() ||
1741  (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective() && MBB.isEndSection()))
1742  OutStreamer->emitLabel(MBB.getEndSymbol());
1743 
1744  if (MBB.isEndSection()) {
1745  // The size directive for the section containing the entry block is
1746  // handled separately by the function section.
1747  if (!MBB.sameSection(&MF->front())) {
1748  if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective()) {
1749  // Emit the size directive for the basic block section.
1750  const MCExpr *SizeExp = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(
1751  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB.getEndSymbol(), OutContext),
1752  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentSectionBeginSym, OutContext),
1753  OutContext);
1754  OutStreamer->emitELFSize(CurrentSectionBeginSym, SizeExp);
1755  }
1756  MBBSectionRanges[MBB.getSectionIDNum()] =
1757  MBBSectionRange{CurrentSectionBeginSym, MBB.getEndSymbol()};
1758  }
1759  }
1760  emitBasicBlockEnd(MBB);
1761 
1762  if (CanDoExtraAnalysis) {
1763  // Skip empty blocks.
1764  if (MBB.empty())
1765  continue;
1766 
1767  MachineOptimizationRemarkAnalysis R(DEBUG_TYPE, "InstructionMix",
1768  MBB.begin()->getDebugLoc(), &MBB);
1769 
1770  // Generate instruction mix remark. First, sort counts in descending order
1771  // by count and name.
1772  SmallVector<std::pair<StringRef, unsigned>, 128> MnemonicVec;
1773  for (auto &KV : MnemonicCounts)
1774  MnemonicVec.emplace_back(KV.first, KV.second);
1775 
1776  sort(MnemonicVec, [](const std::pair<StringRef, unsigned> &A,
1777  const std::pair<StringRef, unsigned> &B) {
1778  if (A.second > B.second)
1779  return true;
1780  if (A.second == B.second)
1781  return StringRef(A.first) < StringRef(B.first);
1782  return false;
1783  });
1784  R << "BasicBlock: " << ore::NV("BasicBlock", MBB.getName()) << "\n";
1785  for (auto &KV : MnemonicVec) {
1786  auto Name = (Twine("INST_") + getToken(KV.first.trim()).first).str();
1787  R << KV.first << ": " << ore::NV(Name, KV.second) << "\n";
1788  }
1789  ORE->emit(R);
1790  }
1791  }
1792 
1793  EmittedInsts += NumInstsInFunction;
1794  MachineOptimizationRemarkAnalysis R(DEBUG_TYPE, "InstructionCount",
1795  MF->getFunction().getSubprogram(),
1796  &MF->front());
1797  R << ore::NV("NumInstructions", NumInstsInFunction)
1798  << " instructions in function";
1799  ORE->emit(R);
1800 
1801  // If the function is empty and the object file uses .subsections_via_symbols,
1802  // then we need to emit *something* to the function body to prevent the
1803  // labels from collapsing together. Just emit a noop.
1804  // Similarly, don't emit empty functions on Windows either. It can lead to
1805  // duplicate entries (two functions with the same RVA) in the Guard CF Table
1806  // after linking, causing the kernel not to load the binary:
1807  // https://developercommunity.visualstudio.com/content/problem/45366/vc-linker-creates-invalid-dll-with-clang-cl.html
1808  // FIXME: Hide this behind some API in e.g. MCAsmInfo or MCTargetStreamer.
1809  const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple();
1810  if (!HasAnyRealCode && (MAI->hasSubsectionsViaSymbols() ||
1811  (TT.isOSWindows() && TT.isOSBinFormatCOFF()))) {
1812  MCInst Noop = MF->getSubtarget().getInstrInfo()->getNop();
1813 
1814  // Targets can opt-out of emitting the noop here by leaving the opcode
1815  // unspecified.
1816  if (Noop.getOpcode()) {
1817  OutStreamer->AddComment("avoids zero-length function");
1818  emitNops(1);
1819  }
1820  }
1821 
1822  // Switch to the original section in case basic block sections was used.
1823  OutStreamer->switchSection(MF->getSection());
1824 
1825  const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
1826  for (const auto &BB : F) {
1827  if (!BB.hasAddressTaken())
1828  continue;
1829  MCSymbol *Sym = GetBlockAddressSymbol(&BB);
1830  if (Sym->isDefined())
1831  continue;
1832  OutStreamer->AddComment("Address of block that was removed by CodeGen");
1833  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Sym);
1834  }
1835 
1836  // Emit target-specific gunk after the function body.
1837  emitFunctionBodyEnd();
1838 
1839  // Even though wasm supports .type and .size in general, function symbols
1840  // are automatically sized.
1841  bool EmitFunctionSize = MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective() && !TT.isWasm();
1842 
1843  if (needFuncLabels(*MF) || EmitFunctionSize) {
1844  // Create a symbol for the end of function.
1845  CurrentFnEnd = createTempSymbol("func_end");
1846  OutStreamer->emitLabel(CurrentFnEnd);
1847  }
1848 
1849  // If the target wants a .size directive for the size of the function, emit
1850  // it.
1851  if (EmitFunctionSize) {
1852  // We can get the size as difference between the function label and the
1853  // temp label.
1854  const MCExpr *SizeExp = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(
1855  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentFnEnd, OutContext),
1856  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentFnSymForSize, OutContext), OutContext);
1857  OutStreamer->emitELFSize(CurrentFnSym, SizeExp);
1858  if (CurrentFnBeginLocal)
1859  OutStreamer->emitELFSize(CurrentFnBeginLocal, SizeExp);
1860  }
1861 
1862  // Call endBasicBlockSection on the last block now, if it wasn't already
1863  // called.
1864  if (!MF->back().isEndSection()) {
1865  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1866  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1867  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1868  HI.Handler->endBasicBlockSection(MF->back());
1869  }
1870  }
1871  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1872  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1873  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1874  HI.Handler->markFunctionEnd();
1875  }
1876 
1877  MBBSectionRanges[MF->front().getSectionIDNum()] =
1878  MBBSectionRange{CurrentFnBegin, CurrentFnEnd};
1879 
1880  // Print out jump tables referenced by the function.
1881  emitJumpTableInfo();
1882 
1883  // Emit post-function debug and/or EH information.
1884  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
1885  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
1886  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
1887  HI.Handler->endFunction(MF);
1888  }
1889 
1890  // Emit section containing BB address offsets and their metadata, when
1891  // BB labels are requested for this function. Skip empty functions.
1892  if (MF->hasBBLabels() && HasAnyRealCode)
1893  emitBBAddrMapSection(*MF);
1894 
1895  // Emit sections containing instruction and function PCs.
1896  emitPCSections(*MF);
1897 
1898  // Emit section containing stack size metadata.
1899  emitStackSizeSection(*MF);
1900 
1901  // Emit .su file containing function stack size information.
1902  emitStackUsage(*MF);
1903 
1904  emitPatchableFunctionEntries();
1905 
1906  if (isVerbose())
1907  OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << "-- End function\n";
1908 
1909  OutStreamer->addBlankLine();
1910 
1911  // Output MBB numbers, function names, and frequencies if the flag to dump
1912  // MBB profile information has been set
1913  if (MBBProfileDumpFileOutput) {
1914  MachineBlockFrequencyInfo &MBFI =
1915  getAnalysis<LazyMachineBlockFrequencyInfoPass>().getBFI();
1916  for (const auto &MBB : *MF) {
1917  *MBBProfileDumpFileOutput.get()
1918  << MF->getName() << "," << MBB.getNumber() << ","
1919  << MBFI.getBlockFreqRelativeToEntryBlock(&MBB) << "\n";
1920  }
1921  }
1922 }
1923 
1924 /// Compute the number of Global Variables that uses a Constant.
1925 static unsigned getNumGlobalVariableUses(const Constant *C) {
1926  if (!C)
1927  return 0;
1928 
1929  if (isa<GlobalVariable>(C))
1930  return 1;
1931 
1932  unsigned NumUses = 0;
1933  for (const auto *CU : C->users())
1934  NumUses += getNumGlobalVariableUses(dyn_cast<Constant>(CU));
1935 
1936  return NumUses;
1937 }
1938 
1939 /// Only consider global GOT equivalents if at least one user is a
1940 /// cstexpr inside an initializer of another global variables. Also, don't
1941 /// handle cstexpr inside instructions. During global variable emission,
1942 /// candidates are skipped and are emitted later in case at least one cstexpr
1943 /// isn't replaced by a PC relative GOT entry access.
1944 static bool isGOTEquivalentCandidate(const GlobalVariable *GV,
1945  unsigned &NumGOTEquivUsers) {
1946  // Global GOT equivalents are unnamed private globals with a constant
1947  // pointer initializer to another global symbol. They must point to a
1948  // GlobalVariable or Function, i.e., as GlobalValue.
1949  if (!GV->hasGlobalUnnamedAddr() || !GV->hasInitializer() ||
1950  !GV->isConstant() || !GV->isDiscardableIfUnused() ||
1951  !isa<GlobalValue>(GV->getOperand(0)))
1952  return false;
1953 
1954  // To be a got equivalent, at least one of its users need to be a constant
1955  // expression used by another global variable.
1956  for (const auto *U : GV->users())
1957  NumGOTEquivUsers += getNumGlobalVariableUses(dyn_cast<Constant>(U));
1958 
1959  return NumGOTEquivUsers > 0;
1960 }
1961 
1962 /// Unnamed constant global variables solely contaning a pointer to
1963 /// another globals variable is equivalent to a GOT table entry; it contains the
1964 /// the address of another symbol. Optimize it and replace accesses to these
1965 /// "GOT equivalents" by using the GOT entry for the final global instead.
1966 /// Compute GOT equivalent candidates among all global variables to avoid
1967 /// emitting them if possible later on, after it use is replaced by a GOT entry
1968 /// access.
1969 void AsmPrinter::computeGlobalGOTEquivs(Module &M) {
1970  if (!getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel())
1971  return;
1972 
1973  for (const auto &G : M.globals()) {
1974  unsigned NumGOTEquivUsers = 0;
1975  if (!isGOTEquivalentCandidate(&G, NumGOTEquivUsers))
1976  continue;
1977 
1978  const MCSymbol *GOTEquivSym = getSymbol(&G);
1979  GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym] = std::make_pair(&G, NumGOTEquivUsers);
1980  }
1981 }
1982 
1983 /// Constant expressions using GOT equivalent globals may not be eligible
1984 /// for PC relative GOT entry conversion, in such cases we need to emit such
1985 /// globals we previously omitted in EmitGlobalVariable.
1986 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalGOTEquivs() {
1987  if (!getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel())
1988  return;
1989 
1990  SmallVector<const GlobalVariable *, 8> FailedCandidates;
1991  for (auto &I : GlobalGOTEquivs) {
1992  const GlobalVariable *GV = I.second.first;
1993  unsigned Cnt = I.second.second;
1994  if (Cnt)
1995  FailedCandidates.push_back(GV);
1996  }
1997  GlobalGOTEquivs.clear();
1998 
1999  for (const auto *GV : FailedCandidates)
2000  emitGlobalVariable(GV);
2001 }
2002 
2003 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalAlias(Module &M, const GlobalAlias &GA) {
2004  MCSymbol *Name = getSymbol(&GA);
2005  bool IsFunction = GA.getValueType()->isFunctionTy();
2006  // Treat bitcasts of functions as functions also. This is important at least
2007  // on WebAssembly where object and function addresses can't alias each other.
2008  if (!IsFunction)
2009  IsFunction = isa<Function>(GA.getAliasee()->stripPointerCasts());
2010 
2011  // AIX's assembly directive `.set` is not usable for aliasing purpose,
2012  // so AIX has to use the extra-label-at-definition strategy. At this
2013  // point, all the extra label is emitted, we just have to emit linkage for
2014  // those labels.
2015  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatXCOFF()) {
2016  assert(MAI->hasVisibilityOnlyWithLinkage() &&
2017  "Visibility should be handled with emitLinkage() on AIX.");
2018 
2019  // Linkage for alias of global variable has been emitted.
2020  if (isa<GlobalVariable>(GA.getAliaseeObject()))
2021  return;
2022 
2023  emitLinkage(&GA, Name);
2024  // If it's a function, also emit linkage for aliases of function entry
2025  // point.
2026  if (IsFunction)
2027  emitLinkage(&GA,
2028  getObjFileLowering().getFunctionEntryPointSymbol(&GA, TM));
2029  return;
2030  }
2031 
2032  if (GA.hasExternalLinkage() || !MAI->getWeakRefDirective())
2033  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_Global);
2034  else if (GA.hasWeakLinkage() || GA.hasLinkOnceLinkage())
2035  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_WeakReference);
2036  else
2037  assert(GA.hasLocalLinkage() && "Invalid alias linkage");
2038 
2039  // Set the symbol type to function if the alias has a function type.
2040  // This affects codegen when the aliasee is not a function.
2041  if (IsFunction) {
2042  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_ELF_TypeFunction);
2043  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
2044  OutStreamer->beginCOFFSymbolDef(Name);
2045  OutStreamer->emitCOFFSymbolStorageClass(
2046  GA.hasLocalLinkage() ? COFF::IMAGE_SYM_CLASS_STATIC
2047  : COFF::IMAGE_SYM_CLASS_EXTERNAL);
2048  OutStreamer->emitCOFFSymbolType(COFF::IMAGE_SYM_DTYPE_FUNCTION
2049  << COFF::SCT_COMPLEX_TYPE_SHIFT);
2050  OutStreamer->endCOFFSymbolDef();
2051  }
2052  }
2053 
2054  emitVisibility(Name, GA.getVisibility());
2055 
2056  const MCExpr *Expr = lowerConstant(GA.getAliasee());
2057 
2058  if (MAI->hasAltEntry() && isa<MCBinaryExpr>(Expr))
2059  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_AltEntry);
2060 
2061  // Emit the directives as assignments aka .set:
2062  OutStreamer->emitAssignment(Name, Expr);
2063  MCSymbol *LocalAlias = getSymbolPreferLocal(GA);
2064  if (LocalAlias != Name)
2065  OutStreamer->emitAssignment(LocalAlias, Expr);
2066 
2067  // If the aliasee does not correspond to a symbol in the output, i.e. the
2068  // alias is not of an object or the aliased object is private, then set the
2069  // size of the alias symbol from the type of the alias. We don't do this in
2070  // other situations as the alias and aliasee having differing types but same
2071  // size may be intentional.
2072  const GlobalObject *BaseObject = GA.getAliaseeObject();
2073  if (MAI->hasDotTypeDotSizeDirective() && GA.getValueType()->isSized() &&
2074  (!BaseObject || BaseObject->hasPrivateLinkage())) {
2075  const DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
2076  uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(GA.getValueType());
2077  OutStreamer->emitELFSize(Name, MCConstantExpr::create(Size, OutContext));
2078  }
2079 }
2080 
2081 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalIFunc(Module &M, const GlobalIFunc &GI) {
2082  assert(!TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatXCOFF() &&
2083  "IFunc is not supported on AIX.");
2084 
2085  MCSymbol *Name = getSymbol(&GI);
2086 
2087  if (GI.hasExternalLinkage() || !MAI->getWeakRefDirective())
2088  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_Global);
2089  else if (GI.hasWeakLinkage() || GI.hasLinkOnceLinkage())
2090  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_WeakReference);
2091  else
2092  assert(GI.hasLocalLinkage() && "Invalid ifunc linkage");
2093 
2094  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Name, MCSA_ELF_TypeIndFunction);
2095  emitVisibility(Name, GI.getVisibility());
2096 
2097  // Emit the directives as assignments aka .set:
2098  const MCExpr *Expr = lowerConstant(GI.getResolver());
2099  OutStreamer->emitAssignment(Name, Expr);
2100  MCSymbol *LocalAlias = getSymbolPreferLocal(GI);
2101  if (LocalAlias != Name)
2102  OutStreamer->emitAssignment(LocalAlias, Expr);
2103 }
