2105 void AsmPrinter::emitRemarksSection(remarks::RemarkStreamer &RS) {
2106  if (!RS.needsSection())
2107  return;
2108 
2109  remarks::RemarkSerializer &RemarkSerializer = RS.getSerializer();
2110 
2111  std::optional<SmallString<128>> Filename;
2112  if (std::optional<StringRef> FilenameRef = RS.getFilename()) {
2113  Filename = *FilenameRef;
2114  sys::fs::make_absolute(*Filename);
2115  assert(!Filename->empty() && "The filename can't be empty.");
2116  }
2117 
2118  std::string Buf;
2119  raw_string_ostream OS(Buf);
2120  std::unique_ptr<remarks::MetaSerializer> MetaSerializer =
2121  Filename ? RemarkSerializer.metaSerializer(OS, Filename->str())
2122  : RemarkSerializer.metaSerializer(OS);
2123  MetaSerializer->emit();
2124 
2125  // Switch to the remarks section.
2126  MCSection *RemarksSection =
2127  OutContext.getObjectFileInfo()->getRemarksSection();
2128  OutStreamer->switchSection(RemarksSection);
2129 
2130  OutStreamer->emitBinaryData(OS.str());
2131 }
2132 
2133 bool AsmPrinter::doFinalization(Module &M) {
2134  // Set the MachineFunction to nullptr so that we can catch attempted
2135  // accesses to MF specific features at the module level and so that
2136  // we can conditionalize accesses based on whether or not it is nullptr.
2137  MF = nullptr;
2138 
2139  // Gather all GOT equivalent globals in the module. We really need two
2140  // passes over the globals: one to compute and another to avoid its emission
2141  // in EmitGlobalVariable, otherwise we would not be able to handle cases
2142  // where the got equivalent shows up before its use.
2143  computeGlobalGOTEquivs(M);
2144 
2145  // Emit global variables.
2146  for (const auto &G : M.globals())
2147  emitGlobalVariable(&G);
2148 
2149  // Emit remaining GOT equivalent globals.
2150  emitGlobalGOTEquivs();
2151 
2152  const TargetLoweringObjectFile &TLOF = getObjFileLowering();
2153 
2154  // Emit linkage(XCOFF) and visibility info for declarations
2155  for (const Function &F : M) {
2156  if (!F.isDeclarationForLinker())
2157  continue;
2158 
2159  MCSymbol *Name = getSymbol(&F);
2160  // Function getSymbol gives us the function descriptor symbol for XCOFF.
2161 
2162  if (!TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatXCOFF()) {
2163  GlobalValue::VisibilityTypes V = F.getVisibility();
2164  if (V == GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility)
2165  continue;
2166 
2167  emitVisibility(Name, V, false);
2168  continue;
2169  }
2170 
2171  if (F.isIntrinsic())
2172  continue;
2173 
2174  // Handle the XCOFF case.
2175  // Variable `Name` is the function descriptor symbol (see above). Get the
2176  // function entry point symbol.
2177  MCSymbol *FnEntryPointSym = TLOF.getFunctionEntryPointSymbol(&F, TM);
2178  // Emit linkage for the function entry point.
2179  emitLinkage(&F, FnEntryPointSym);
2180 
2181  // Emit linkage for the function descriptor.
2182  emitLinkage(&F, Name);
2183  }
2184 
2185  // Emit the remarks section contents.
2186  // FIXME: Figure out when is the safest time to emit this section. It should
2187  // not come after debug info.
2188  if (remarks::RemarkStreamer *RS = M.getContext().getMainRemarkStreamer())
2189  emitRemarksSection(*RS);
2190 
2191  TLOF.emitModuleMetadata(*OutStreamer, M);
2192 
2193  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
2194  MachineModuleInfoELF &MMIELF = MMI->getObjFileInfo<MachineModuleInfoELF>();
2195 
2196  // Output stubs for external and common global variables.
2197  MachineModuleInfoELF::SymbolListTy Stubs = MMIELF.GetGVStubList();
2198  if (!Stubs.empty()) {
2199  OutStreamer->switchSection(TLOF.getDataSection());
2200  const DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
2201 
2202  emitAlignment(Align(DL.getPointerSize()));
2203  for (const auto &Stub : Stubs) {
2204  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Stub.first);
2205  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(Stub.second.getPointer(),
2206  DL.getPointerSize());
2207  }
2208  }
2209  }
2210 
2211  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatCOFF()) {
2212  MachineModuleInfoCOFF &MMICOFF =
2213  MMI->getObjFileInfo<MachineModuleInfoCOFF>();
2214 
2215  // Output stubs for external and common global variables.
2216  MachineModuleInfoCOFF::SymbolListTy Stubs = MMICOFF.GetGVStubList();
2217  if (!Stubs.empty()) {
2218  const DataLayout &DL = M.getDataLayout();
2219 
2220  for (const auto &Stub : Stubs) {
2221  SmallString<256> SectionName = StringRef(".rdata$");
2222  SectionName += Stub.first->getName();
2223  OutStreamer->switchSection(OutContext.getCOFFSection(
2224  SectionName,
2225  COFF::IMAGE_SCN_CNT_INITIALIZED_DATA | COFF::IMAGE_SCN_MEM_READ |
2226  COFF::IMAGE_SCN_LNK_COMDAT,
2227  SectionKind::getReadOnly(), Stub.first->getName(),
2228  COFF::IMAGE_COMDAT_SELECT_ANY));
2229  emitAlignment(Align(DL.getPointerSize()));
2230  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Stub.first, MCSA_Global);
2231  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Stub.first);
2232  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(Stub.second.getPointer(),
2233  DL.getPointerSize());
2234  }
2235  }
2236  }
2237 
2238  // This needs to happen before emitting debug information since that can end
2239  // arbitrary sections.
2240  if (auto *TS = OutStreamer->getTargetStreamer())
2241  TS->emitConstantPools();
2242 
2243  // Emit Stack maps before any debug info. Mach-O requires that no data or
2244  // text sections come after debug info has been emitted. This matters for
2245  // stack maps as they are arbitrary data, and may even have a custom format
2246  // through user plugins.
2247  emitStackMaps();
2248 
2249  // Finalize debug and EH information.
2250  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
2251  NamedRegionTimer T(HI.TimerName, HI.TimerDescription, HI.TimerGroupName,
2252  HI.TimerGroupDescription, TimePassesIsEnabled);
2253  HI.Handler->endModule();
2254  }
2255 
2256  // This deletes all the ephemeral handlers that AsmPrinter added, while
2257  // keeping all the user-added handlers alive until the AsmPrinter is
2258  // destroyed.
2259  Handlers.erase(Handlers.begin() + NumUserHandlers, Handlers.end());
2260  DD = nullptr;
2261 
2262  // If the target wants to know about weak references, print them all.
2263  if (MAI->getWeakRefDirective()) {
2264  // FIXME: This is not lazy, it would be nice to only print weak references
2265  // to stuff that is actually used. Note that doing so would require targets
2266  // to notice uses in operands (due to constant exprs etc). This should
2267  // happen with the MC stuff eventually.
2268 
2269  // Print out module-level global objects here.
2270  for (const auto &GO : M.global_objects()) {
2271  if (!GO.hasExternalWeakLinkage())
2272  continue;
2273  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(getSymbol(&GO), MCSA_WeakReference);
2274  }
2275  if (shouldEmitWeakSwiftAsyncExtendedFramePointerFlags()) {
2276  auto SymbolName = "swift_async_extendedFramePointerFlags";
2277  auto Global = M.getGlobalVariable(SymbolName);
2278  if (!Global) {
2279  auto Int8PtrTy = Type::getInt8PtrTy(M.getContext());
2280  Global = new GlobalVariable(M, Int8PtrTy, false,
2281  GlobalValue::ExternalWeakLinkage, nullptr,
2282  SymbolName);
2283  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(getSymbol(Global), MCSA_WeakReference);
2284  }
2285  }
2286  }
2287 
2288  // Print aliases in topological order, that is, for each alias a = b,
2289  // b must be printed before a.
2290  // This is because on some targets (e.g. PowerPC) linker expects aliases in
2291  // such an order to generate correct TOC information.
2292  SmallVector<const GlobalAlias *, 16> AliasStack;
2293  SmallPtrSet<const GlobalAlias *, 16> AliasVisited;
2294  for (const auto &Alias : M.aliases()) {
2295  if (Alias.hasAvailableExternallyLinkage())
2296  continue;
2297  for (const GlobalAlias *Cur = &Alias; Cur;
2298  Cur = dyn_cast<GlobalAlias>(Cur->getAliasee())) {
2299  if (!AliasVisited.insert(Cur).second)
2300  break;
2301  AliasStack.push_back(Cur);
2302  }
2303  for (const GlobalAlias *AncestorAlias : llvm::reverse(AliasStack))
2304  emitGlobalAlias(M, *AncestorAlias);
2305  AliasStack.clear();
2306  }
2307  for (const auto &IFunc : M.ifuncs())
2308  emitGlobalIFunc(M, IFunc);
2309 
2310  GCModuleInfo *MI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<GCModuleInfo>();
2311  assert(MI && "AsmPrinter didn't require GCModuleInfo?");
2312  for (GCModuleInfo::iterator I = MI->end(), E = MI->begin(); I != E; )
2313  if (GCMetadataPrinter *MP = getOrCreateGCPrinter(**--I))
2314  MP->finishAssembly(M, *MI, *this);
2315 
2316  // Emit llvm.ident metadata in an '.ident' directive.
2317  emitModuleIdents(M);
2318 
2319  // Emit bytes for llvm.commandline metadata.
2320  emitModuleCommandLines(M);
2321 
2322  // Emit .note.GNU-split-stack and .note.GNU-no-split-stack sections if
2323  // split-stack is used.
2324  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF() && HasSplitStack) {
2325  OutStreamer->switchSection(OutContext.getELFSection(".note.GNU-split-stack",
2326  ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, 0));
2327  if (HasNoSplitStack)
2328  OutStreamer->switchSection(OutContext.getELFSection(
2329  ".note.GNU-no-split-stack", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, 0));
2330  }
2331 
2332  // If we don't have any trampolines, then we don't require stack memory
2333  // to be executable. Some targets have a directive to declare this.
2334  Function *InitTrampolineIntrinsic = M.getFunction("llvm.init.trampoline");
2335  if (!InitTrampolineIntrinsic || InitTrampolineIntrinsic->use_empty())
2336  if (MCSection *S = MAI->getNonexecutableStackSection(OutContext))
2337  OutStreamer->switchSection(S);
2338 
2339  if (TM.Options.EmitAddrsig) {
2340  // Emit address-significance attributes for all globals.
2341  OutStreamer->emitAddrsig();
2342  for (const GlobalValue &GV : M.global_values()) {
2343  if (!GV.use_empty() && !GV.isThreadLocal() &&
2344  !GV.hasDLLImportStorageClass() && !GV.getName().startswith("llvm.") &&
2345  !GV.hasAtLeastLocalUnnamedAddr())
2346  OutStreamer->emitAddrsigSym(getSymbol(&GV));
2347  }
2348  }
2349 
2350  // Emit symbol partition specifications (ELF only).
2351  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
2352  unsigned UniqueID = 0;
2353  for (const GlobalValue &GV : M.global_values()) {
2354  if (!GV.hasPartition() || GV.isDeclarationForLinker() ||
2355  GV.getVisibility() != GlobalValue::DefaultVisibility)
2356  continue;
2357 
2358  OutStreamer->switchSection(
2359  OutContext.getELFSection(".llvm_sympart", ELF::SHT_LLVM_SYMPART, 0, 0,
2360  "", false, ++UniqueID, nullptr));
2361  OutStreamer->emitBytes(GV.getPartition());
2362  OutStreamer->emitZeros(1);
2363  OutStreamer->emitValue(
2364  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(&GV), OutContext),
2365  MAI->getCodePointerSize());
2366  }
2367  }
2368 
2369  // Allow the target to emit any magic that it wants at the end of the file,
2370  // after everything else has gone out.
2371  emitEndOfAsmFile(M);
2372 
2373  MMI = nullptr;
2374  AddrLabelSymbols = nullptr;
2375 
2376  OutStreamer->finish();
2377  OutStreamer->reset();
2378  OwnedMLI.reset();
2379  OwnedMDT.reset();
2380 
2381  return false;
2382 }

2384 MCSymbol *AsmPrinter::getMBBExceptionSym(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) {
2385  auto Res = MBBSectionExceptionSyms.try_emplace(MBB.getSectionIDNum());
2386  if (Res.second)
2387  Res.first->second = createTempSymbol("exception");
2388  return Res.first->second;

2391 void AsmPrinter::SetupMachineFunction(MachineFunction &MF) {
2392  this->MF = &MF;
2393  const Function &F = MF.getFunction();
2394 
2395  // Record that there are split-stack functions, so we will emit a special
2396  // section to tell the linker.
2397  if (MF.shouldSplitStack()) {
2398  HasSplitStack = true;
2399 
2400  if (!MF.getFrameInfo().needsSplitStackProlog())
2401  HasNoSplitStack = true;
2402  } else
2403  HasNoSplitStack = true;
2404 
2405  // Get the function symbol.
2406  if (!MAI->needsFunctionDescriptors()) {
2407  CurrentFnSym = getSymbol(&MF.getFunction());
2408  } else {
2409  assert(TM.getTargetTriple().isOSAIX() &&
2410  "Only AIX uses the function descriptor hooks.");
2411  // AIX is unique here in that the name of the symbol emitted for the
2412  // function body does not have the same name as the source function's
2413  // C-linkage name.
2414  assert(CurrentFnDescSym && "The function descriptor symbol needs to be"
2415  " initalized first.");
2416 
2417  // Get the function entry point symbol.
2418  CurrentFnSym = getObjFileLowering().getFunctionEntryPointSymbol(&F, TM);
2419  }
2420 
2421  CurrentFnSymForSize = CurrentFnSym;
2422  CurrentFnBegin = nullptr;
2423  CurrentFnBeginLocal = nullptr;
2424  CurrentSectionBeginSym = nullptr;
2425  MBBSectionRanges.clear();
2426  MBBSectionExceptionSyms.clear();
2427  bool NeedsLocalForSize = MAI->needsLocalForSize();
2428  if (F.hasFnAttribute("patchable-function-entry") ||
2429  F.hasFnAttribute("function-instrument") ||
2430  F.hasFnAttribute("xray-instruction-threshold") ||
2431  needFuncLabels(MF) || NeedsLocalForSize ||
2432  MF.getTarget().Options.EmitStackSizeSection || MF.hasBBLabels()) {
2433  CurrentFnBegin = createTempSymbol("func_begin");
2434  if (NeedsLocalForSize)
2435  CurrentFnSymForSize = CurrentFnBegin;
2436  }
2437 
2438  ORE = &getAnalysis<MachineOptimizationRemarkEmitterPass>().getORE();
2439 }

2441 namespace {

2443 // Keep track the alignment, constpool entries per Section.
2444  struct SectionCPs {
2445  MCSection *S;
2446  Align Alignment;
2447  SmallVector<unsigned, 4> CPEs;
2448 
2449  SectionCPs(MCSection *s, Align a) : S(s), Alignment(a) {}
2450  };
2451 
2452 } // end anonymous namespace
2453 
2454 /// EmitConstantPool - Print to the current output stream assembly
2455 /// representations of the constants in the constant pool MCP. This is
2456 /// used to print out constants which have been "spilled to memory" by
2457 /// the code generator.
2458 void AsmPrinter::emitConstantPool() {
2459  const MachineConstantPool *MCP = MF->getConstantPool();
2460  const std::vector<MachineConstantPoolEntry> &CP = MCP->getConstants();
2461  if (CP.empty()) return;
2462 
2463  // Calculate sections for constant pool entries. We collect entries to go into
2464  // the same section together to reduce amount of section switch statements.
2465  SmallVector<SectionCPs, 4> CPSections;
2466  for (unsigned i = 0, e = CP.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2467  const MachineConstantPoolEntry &CPE = CP[i];
2468  Align Alignment = CPE.getAlign();
2469 
2470  SectionKind Kind = CPE.getSectionKind(&getDataLayout());
2471 
2472  const Constant *C = nullptr;
2473  if (!CPE.isMachineConstantPoolEntry())
2474  C = CPE.Val.ConstVal;
2475 
2476  MCSection *S = getObjFileLowering().getSectionForConstant(
2477  getDataLayout(), Kind, C, Alignment);
2478 
2479  // The number of sections are small, just do a linear search from the
2480  // last section to the first.
2481  bool Found = false;
2482  unsigned SecIdx = CPSections.size();
2483  while (SecIdx != 0) {
2484  if (CPSections[--SecIdx].S == S) {
2485  Found = true;
2486  break;
2487  }
2488  }
2489  if (!Found) {
2490  SecIdx = CPSections.size();
2491  CPSections.push_back(SectionCPs(S, Alignment));
2492  }
2493 
2494  if (Alignment > CPSections[SecIdx].Alignment)
2495  CPSections[SecIdx].Alignment = Alignment;
2496  CPSections[SecIdx].CPEs.push_back(i);
2497  }
2498 
2499  // Now print stuff into the calculated sections.
2500  const MCSection *CurSection = nullptr;
2501  unsigned Offset = 0;
2502  for (unsigned i = 0, e = CPSections.size(); i != e; ++i) {
2503  for (unsigned j = 0, ee = CPSections[i].CPEs.size(); j != ee; ++j) {
2504  unsigned CPI = CPSections[i].CPEs[j];
2505  MCSymbol *Sym = GetCPISymbol(CPI);
2506  if (!Sym->isUndefined())
2507  continue;
2508 
2509  if (CurSection != CPSections[i].S) {
2510  OutStreamer->switchSection(CPSections[i].S);
2511  emitAlignment(Align(CPSections[i].Alignment));
2512  CurSection = CPSections[i].S;
2513  Offset = 0;
2514  }
2515 
2516  MachineConstantPoolEntry CPE = CP[CPI];
2517 
2518  // Emit inter-object padding for alignment.
2519  unsigned NewOffset = alignTo(Offset, CPE.getAlign());
2520  OutStreamer->emitZeros(NewOffset - Offset);
2521 
2522  Offset = NewOffset + CPE.getSizeInBytes(getDataLayout());
2523 
2524  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Sym);
2525  if (CPE.isMachineConstantPoolEntry())
2526  emitMachineConstantPoolValue(CPE.Val.MachineCPVal);
2527  else
2528  emitGlobalConstant(getDataLayout(), CPE.Val.ConstVal);
2529  }
2530  }
2531 }
2532 
2533 // Print assembly representations of the jump tables used by the current
2534 // function.
2535 void AsmPrinter::emitJumpTableInfo() {
2536  const DataLayout &DL = MF->getDataLayout();
2537  const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI = MF->getJumpTableInfo();
2538  if (!MJTI) return;
2539  if (MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Inline) return;
2540  const std::vector<MachineJumpTableEntry> &JT = MJTI->getJumpTables();
2541  if (JT.empty()) return;
2542 
2543  // Pick the directive to use to print the jump table entries, and switch to
2544  // the appropriate section.
2545  const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
2546  const TargetLoweringObjectFile &TLOF = getObjFileLowering();
2547  bool JTInDiffSection = !TLOF.shouldPutJumpTableInFunctionSection(
2548  MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32,
2549  F);
2550  if (JTInDiffSection) {
2551  // Drop it in the readonly section.
2552  MCSection *ReadOnlySection = TLOF.getSectionForJumpTable(F, TM);
2553  OutStreamer->switchSection(ReadOnlySection);
2554  }
2555 
2556  emitAlignment(Align(MJTI->getEntryAlignment(DL)));
2557 
2558  // Jump tables in code sections are marked with a data_region directive
2559  // where that's supported.
2560  if (!JTInDiffSection)
2561  OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionJT32);
2562 
2563  for (unsigned JTI = 0, e = JT.size(); JTI != e; ++JTI) {
2564  const std::vector<MachineBasicBlock*> &JTBBs = JT[JTI].MBBs;
2565 
2566  // If this jump table was deleted, ignore it.
2567  if (JTBBs.empty()) continue;
2568 
2569  // For the EK_LabelDifference32 entry, if using .set avoids a relocation,
2570  /// emit a .set directive for each unique entry.
2571  if (MJTI->getEntryKind() == MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32 &&
2572  MAI->doesSetDirectiveSuppressReloc()) {
2573  SmallPtrSet<const MachineBasicBlock*, 16> EmittedSets;
2574  const TargetLowering *TLI = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
2575  const MCExpr *Base = TLI->getPICJumpTableRelocBaseExpr(MF,JTI,OutContext);
2576  for (const MachineBasicBlock *MBB : JTBBs) {
2577  if (!EmittedSets.insert(MBB).second)
2578  continue;
2579 
2580  // .set LJTSet, LBB32-base
2581  const MCExpr *LHS =
2582  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext);
2583  OutStreamer->emitAssignment(GetJTSetSymbol(JTI, MBB->getNumber()),
2584  MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LHS, Base,
2585  OutContext));
2586  }
2587  }
2588 
2589  // On some targets (e.g. Darwin) we want to emit two consecutive labels
2590  // before each jump table. The first label is never referenced, but tells
2591  // the assembler and linker the extents of the jump table object. The
2592  // second label is actually referenced by the code.
2593  if (JTInDiffSection && DL.hasLinkerPrivateGlobalPrefix())
2594  // FIXME: This doesn't have to have any specific name, just any randomly
2595  // named and numbered local label started with 'l' would work. Simplify
2596  // GetJTISymbol.
2597  OutStreamer->emitLabel(GetJTISymbol(JTI, true));
2598 
2599  MCSymbol* JTISymbol = GetJTISymbol(JTI);
2600  OutStreamer->emitLabel(JTISymbol);
2601 
2602  for (const MachineBasicBlock *MBB : JTBBs)
2603  emitJumpTableEntry(MJTI, MBB, JTI);
2604  }
2605  if (!JTInDiffSection)
2606  OutStreamer->emitDataRegion(MCDR_DataRegionEnd);
2607 }
2608 
2609 /// EmitJumpTableEntry - Emit a jump table entry for the specified MBB to the
2610 /// current stream.
2611 void AsmPrinter::emitJumpTableEntry(const MachineJumpTableInfo *MJTI,
2612  const MachineBasicBlock *MBB,
2613  unsigned UID) const {
2614  assert(MBB && MBB->getNumber() >= 0 && "Invalid basic block");
2615  const MCExpr *Value = nullptr;
2616  switch (MJTI->getEntryKind()) {
2617  case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Inline:
2618  llvm_unreachable("Cannot emit EK_Inline jump table entry");
2619  case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_Custom32:
2620  Value = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering()->LowerCustomJumpTableEntry(
2621  MJTI, MBB, UID, OutContext);
2622  break;
2623  case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_BlockAddress:
2624  // EK_BlockAddress - Each entry is a plain address of block, e.g.:
2625  // .word LBB123
2626  Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext);
2627  break;
2628  case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel32BlockAddress: {
2629  // EK_GPRel32BlockAddress - Each entry is an address of block, encoded
2630  // with a relocation as gp-relative, e.g.:
2631  // .gprel32 LBB123
2632  MCSymbol *MBBSym = MBB->getSymbol();
2633  OutStreamer->emitGPRel32Value(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBBSym, OutContext));
2634  return;
2635  }
2636 
2637  case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_GPRel64BlockAddress: {
2638  // EK_GPRel64BlockAddress - Each entry is an address of block, encoded
2639  // with a relocation as gp-relative, e.g.:
2640  // .gpdword LBB123
2641  MCSymbol *MBBSym = MBB->getSymbol();
2642  OutStreamer->emitGPRel64Value(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBBSym, OutContext));
2643  return;
2644  }
2645 
2646  case MachineJumpTableInfo::EK_LabelDifference32: {
2647  // Each entry is the address of the block minus the address of the jump
2648  // table. This is used for PIC jump tables where gprel32 is not supported.
2649  // e.g.:
2650  // .word LBB123 - LJTI1_2
2651  // If the .set directive avoids relocations, this is emitted as:
2652  // .set L4_5_set_123, LBB123 - LJTI1_2
2653  // .word L4_5_set_123
2654  if (MAI->doesSetDirectiveSuppressReloc()) {
2655  Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GetJTSetSymbol(UID, MBB->getNumber()),
2656  OutContext);
2657  break;
2658  }
2659  Value = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(MBB->getSymbol(), OutContext);
2660  const TargetLowering *TLI = MF->getSubtarget().getTargetLowering();
2661  const MCExpr *Base = TLI->getPICJumpTableRelocBaseExpr(MF, UID, OutContext);
2662  Value = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(Value, Base, OutContext);
2663  break;
2664  }
2665  }
2666 
2667  assert(Value && "Unknown entry kind!");
2668 
2669  unsigned EntrySize = MJTI->getEntrySize(getDataLayout());
2670  OutStreamer->emitValue(Value, EntrySize);
2671 }
2672 
2673 /// EmitSpecialLLVMGlobal - Check to see if the specified global is a
2674 /// special global used by LLVM. If so, emit it and return true, otherwise
2675 /// do nothing and return false.
2676 bool AsmPrinter::emitSpecialLLVMGlobal(const GlobalVariable *GV) {
2677  if (GV->getName() == "llvm.used") {
2678  if (MAI->hasNoDeadStrip()) // No need to emit this at all.
2679  emitLLVMUsedList(cast<ConstantArray>(GV->getInitializer()));
2680  return true;
2681  }
2682 
2683  // Ignore debug and non-emitted data. This handles llvm.compiler.used.
2684  if (GV->getSection() == "llvm.metadata" ||
2685  GV->hasAvailableExternallyLinkage())
2686  return true;
2687 
2688  if (!GV->hasAppendingLinkage()) return false;
2689 
2690  assert(GV->hasInitializer() && "Not a special LLVM global!");
2691 
2692  if (GV->getName() == "llvm.global_ctors") {
2693  emitXXStructorList(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(),
2694  /* isCtor */ true);
2695 
2696  return true;
2697  }
2698 
2699  if (GV->getName() == "llvm.global_dtors") {
2700  emitXXStructorList(GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), GV->getInitializer(),
2701  /* isCtor */ false);
2702 
2703  return true;
2704  }
2705 
2706  report_fatal_error("unknown special variable");
2707 }

2709 /// EmitLLVMUsedList - For targets that define a MAI::UsedDirective, mark each
2710 /// global in the specified llvm.used list.
2711 void AsmPrinter::emitLLVMUsedList(const ConstantArray *InitList) {
2712  // Should be an array of 'i8*'.
2713  for (unsigned i = 0, e = InitList->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2714  const GlobalValue *GV =
2715  dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(InitList->getOperand(i)->stripPointerCasts());
2716  if (GV)
2717  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(getSymbol(GV), MCSA_NoDeadStrip);
2718  }
2719 }
2720 
2721 void AsmPrinter::preprocessXXStructorList(const DataLayout &DL,
2722  const Constant *List,
2723  SmallVector<Structor, 8> &Structors) {
2724  // Should be an array of '{ i32, void ()*, i8* }' structs. The first value is
2725  // the init priority.
2726  if (!isa<ConstantArray>(List))
2727  return;
2728 
2729  // Gather the structors in a form that's convenient for sorting by priority.
2730  for (Value *O : cast<ConstantArray>(List)->operands()) {
2731  auto *CS = cast<ConstantStruct>(O);
2732  if (CS->getOperand(1)->isNullValue())
2733  break; // Found a null terminator, skip the rest.
2734  ConstantInt *Priority = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CS->getOperand(0));
2735  if (!Priority)
2736  continue; // Malformed.
2737  Structors.push_back(Structor());
2738  Structor &S = Structors.back();
2739  S.Priority = Priority->getLimitedValue(65535);
2740  S.Func = CS->getOperand(1);
2741  if (!CS->getOperand(2)->isNullValue()) {
2742  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSAIX())
2743  llvm::report_fatal_error(
2744  "associated data of XXStructor list is not yet supported on AIX");
2745  S.ComdatKey =
2746  dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(CS->getOperand(2)->stripPointerCasts());
2747  }
2748  }
2749 
2750  // Emit the function pointers in the target-specific order
2751  llvm::stable_sort(Structors, [](const Structor &L, const Structor &R) {
2752  return L.Priority < R.Priority;
2753  });
2754 }
2755 
2756 /// EmitXXStructorList - Emit the ctor or dtor list taking into account the init
2757 /// priority.
2758 void AsmPrinter::emitXXStructorList(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *List,
2759  bool IsCtor) {
2760  SmallVector<Structor, 8> Structors;
2761  preprocessXXStructorList(DL, List, Structors);
2762  if (Structors.empty())
2763  return;
2764 
2765  // Emit the structors in reverse order if we are using the .ctor/.dtor
2766  // initialization scheme.
2767  if (!TM.Options.UseInitArray)
2768  std::reverse(Structors.begin(), Structors.end());
2769 
2770  const Align Align = DL.getPointerPrefAlignment();
2771  for (Structor &S : Structors) {
2772  const TargetLoweringObjectFile &Obj = getObjFileLowering();
2773  const MCSymbol *KeySym = nullptr;
2774  if (GlobalValue *GV = S.ComdatKey) {
2775  if (GV->isDeclarationForLinker())
2776  // If the associated variable is not defined in this module
2777  // (it might be available_externally, or have been an
2778  // available_externally definition that was dropped by the
2779  // EliminateAvailableExternally pass), some other TU
2780  // will provide its dynamic initializer.
2781  continue;
2782 
2783  KeySym = getSymbol(GV);
2784  }
2785 
2786  MCSection *OutputSection =
2787  (IsCtor ? Obj.getStaticCtorSection(S.Priority, KeySym)
2788  : Obj.getStaticDtorSection(S.Priority, KeySym));
2789  OutStreamer->switchSection(OutputSection);
2790  if (OutStreamer->getCurrentSection() != OutStreamer->getPreviousSection())
2791  emitAlignment(Align);
2792  emitXXStructor(DL, S.Func);
2793  }
2794 }

2796 void AsmPrinter::emitModuleIdents(Module &M) {
2797  if (!MAI->hasIdentDirective())
2798  return;
2799 
2800  if (const NamedMDNode *NMD = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.ident")) {
2801  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NMD->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2802  const MDNode *N = NMD->getOperand(i);
2803  assert(N->getNumOperands() == 1 &&
2804  "llvm.ident metadata entry can have only one operand");
2805  const MDString *S = cast<MDString>(N->getOperand(0));
2806  OutStreamer->emitIdent(S->getString());
2807  }
2808  }
2809 }

2811 void AsmPrinter::emitModuleCommandLines(Module &M) {
2812  MCSection *CommandLine = getObjFileLowering().getSectionForCommandLines();
2813  if (!CommandLine)
2814  return;
2815 
2816  const NamedMDNode *NMD = M.getNamedMetadata("llvm.commandline");
2817  if (!NMD || !NMD->getNumOperands())
2818  return;
2819 
2820  OutStreamer->pushSection();
2821  OutStreamer->switchSection(CommandLine);
2822  OutStreamer->emitZeros(1);
2823  for (unsigned i = 0, e = NMD->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i) {
2824  const MDNode *N = NMD->getOperand(i);
2825  assert(N->getNumOperands() == 1 &&
2826  "llvm.commandline metadata entry can have only one operand");
2827  const MDString *S = cast<MDString>(N->getOperand(0));
2828  OutStreamer->emitBytes(S->getString());
2829  OutStreamer->emitZeros(1);
2830  }
2831  OutStreamer->popSection();
2832 }

2869 /// Emit something like ".long Hi-Lo" where the size in bytes of the directive

2883 /// EmitLabelPlusOffset - Emit something like ".long Label+Offset"
2884 /// where the size in bytes of the directive is specified by Size and Label
2885 /// specifies the label. This implicitly uses .set if it is available.
2886 void AsmPrinter::emitLabelPlusOffset(const MCSymbol *Label, uint64_t Offset,
2887  unsigned Size,
2888  bool IsSectionRelative) const {
2889  if (MAI->needsDwarfSectionOffsetDirective() && IsSectionRelative) {
2890  OutStreamer->emitCOFFSecRel32(Label, Offset);
2891  if (Size > 4)
2892  OutStreamer->emitZeros(Size - 4);
2893  return;
2894  }
2895 
2896  // Emit Label+Offset (or just Label if Offset is zero)
2897  const MCExpr *Expr = MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Label, OutContext);
2898  if (Offset)
2899  Expr = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(
2900  Expr, MCConstantExpr::create(Offset, OutContext), OutContext);
2901 
2902  OutStreamer->emitValue(Expr, Size);
2903 }

2907 // EmitAlignment - Emit an alignment directive to the specified power of
2908 // two boundary. If a global value is specified, and if that global has
2909 // an explicit alignment requested, it will override the alignment request
2910 // if required for correctness.
2911 void AsmPrinter::emitAlignment(Align Alignment, const GlobalObject *GV,
2912  unsigned MaxBytesToEmit) const {
2913  if (GV)
2914  Alignment = getGVAlignment(GV, GV->getParent()->getDataLayout(), Alignment);
2915 
2916  if (Alignment == Align(1))
2917  return; // 1-byte aligned: no need to emit alignment.
2918 
2919  if (getCurrentSection()->getKind().isText()) {
2920  const MCSubtargetInfo *STI = nullptr;
2921  if (this->MF)
2922  STI = &getSubtargetInfo();
2923  else
2924  STI = TM.getMCSubtargetInfo();
2925  OutStreamer->emitCodeAlignment(Alignment, STI, MaxBytesToEmit);
2926  } else
2927  OutStreamer->emitValueToAlignment(Alignment, 0, 1, MaxBytesToEmit);
2928 }

2933 
2934 const MCExpr *AsmPrinter::lowerConstant(const Constant *CV) {
2935  MCContext &Ctx = OutContext;
2936 
2937  if (CV->isNullValue() || isa<UndefValue>(CV))
2938  return MCConstantExpr::create(0, Ctx);
2939 
2940  if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CV))
2941  return MCConstantExpr::create(CI->getZExtValue(), Ctx);
2942 
2943  if (const GlobalValue *GV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(CV))
2944  return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(GV), Ctx);
2945 
2946  if (const BlockAddress *BA = dyn_cast<BlockAddress>(CV))
2947  return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(GetBlockAddressSymbol(BA), Ctx);
2948 
2949  if (const auto *Equiv = dyn_cast<DSOLocalEquivalent>(CV))
2950  return getObjFileLowering().lowerDSOLocalEquivalent(Equiv, TM);
2951 
2952  if (const NoCFIValue *NC = dyn_cast<NoCFIValue>(CV))
2953  return MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(NC->getGlobalValue()), Ctx);
2954 
2955  const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(CV);
2956  if (!CE) {
2957  llvm_unreachable("Unknown constant value to lower!");
2958  }
2959 
2960  // The constant expression opcodes are limited to those that are necessary
2961  // to represent relocations on supported targets. Expressions involving only
2962  // constant addresses are constant folded instead.
2963  switch (CE->getOpcode()) {
2964  default:
2965  break; // Error
2966  case Instruction::AddrSpaceCast: {
2967  const Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0);
2968  unsigned DstAS = CE->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
2969  unsigned SrcAS = Op->getType()->getPointerAddressSpace();
2970  if (TM.isNoopAddrSpaceCast(SrcAS, DstAS))
2971  return lowerConstant(Op);
2972 
2973  break; // Error
2974  }
2975  case Instruction::GetElementPtr: {
2976  // Generate a symbolic expression for the byte address
2977  APInt OffsetAI(getDataLayout().getPointerTypeSizeInBits(CE->getType()), 0);
2978  cast<GEPOperator>(CE)->accumulateConstantOffset(getDataLayout(), OffsetAI);
2979 
2980  const MCExpr *Base = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0));
2981  if (!OffsetAI)
2982  return Base;
2983 
2984  int64_t Offset = OffsetAI.getSExtValue();
2985  return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(Base, MCConstantExpr::create(Offset, Ctx),
2986  Ctx);
2987  }
2988 
2989  case Instruction::Trunc:
2990  // We emit the value and depend on the assembler to truncate the generated
2991  // expression properly. This is important for differences between
2992  // blockaddress labels. Since the two labels are in the same function, it
2993  // is reasonable to treat their delta as a 32-bit value.
2994  [[fallthrough]];
2995  case Instruction::BitCast:
2996  return lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0));
2997 
2998  case Instruction::IntToPtr: {
2999  const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout();
3000 
3001  // Handle casts to pointers by changing them into casts to the appropriate
3002  // integer type. This promotes constant folding and simplifies this code.
3003  Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0);
3004  Op = ConstantExpr::getIntegerCast(Op, DL.getIntPtrType(CV->getType()),
3005  false/*ZExt*/);
3006  return lowerConstant(Op);
3007  }
3008 
3009  case Instruction::PtrToInt: {
3010  const DataLayout &DL = getDataLayout();
3011 
3012  // Support only foldable casts to/from pointers that can be eliminated by
3013  // changing the pointer to the appropriately sized integer type.
3014  Constant *Op = CE->getOperand(0);
3015  Type *Ty = CE->getType();
3016 
3017  const MCExpr *OpExpr = lowerConstant(Op);
3018 
3019  // We can emit the pointer value into this slot if the slot is an
3020  // integer slot equal to the size of the pointer.
3021  //
3022  // If the pointer is larger than the resultant integer, then
3023  // as with Trunc just depend on the assembler to truncate it.
3024  if (DL.getTypeAllocSize(Ty).getFixedValue() <=
3025  DL.getTypeAllocSize(Op->getType()).getFixedValue())
3026  return OpExpr;
3027 
3028  break; // Error
3029  }
3030 
3031  case Instruction::Sub: {
3032  GlobalValue *LHSGV;
3033  APInt LHSOffset;
3034  DSOLocalEquivalent *DSOEquiv;
3035  if (IsConstantOffsetFromGlobal(CE->getOperand(0), LHSGV, LHSOffset,
3036  getDataLayout(), &DSOEquiv)) {
3037  GlobalValue *RHSGV;
3038  APInt RHSOffset;
3039  if (IsConstantOffsetFromGlobal(CE->getOperand(1), RHSGV, RHSOffset,
3040  getDataLayout())) {
3041  const MCExpr *RelocExpr =
3042  getObjFileLowering().lowerRelativeReference(LHSGV, RHSGV, TM);
3043  if (!RelocExpr) {
3044  const MCExpr *LHSExpr =
3045  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(LHSGV), Ctx);
3046  if (DSOEquiv &&
3047  getObjFileLowering().supportDSOLocalEquivalentLowering())
3048  LHSExpr =
3049  getObjFileLowering().lowerDSOLocalEquivalent(DSOEquiv, TM);
3050  RelocExpr = MCBinaryExpr::createSub(
3051  LHSExpr, MCSymbolRefExpr::create(getSymbol(RHSGV), Ctx), Ctx);
3052  }
3053  int64_t Addend = (LHSOffset - RHSOffset).getSExtValue();
3054  if (Addend != 0)
3055  RelocExpr = MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(
3056  RelocExpr, MCConstantExpr::create(Addend, Ctx), Ctx);
3057  return RelocExpr;
3058  }
3059  }
3060 
3061  const MCExpr *LHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0));
3062  const MCExpr *RHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(1));
3063  return MCBinaryExpr::createSub(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
3064  break;
3065  }
3066 
3067  case Instruction::Add: {
3068  const MCExpr *LHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(0));
3069  const MCExpr *RHS = lowerConstant(CE->getOperand(1));
3070  return MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(LHS, RHS, Ctx);
3071  }
3072  }
3073 
3074  // If the code isn't optimized, there may be outstanding folding
3075  // opportunities. Attempt to fold the expression using DataLayout as a
3076  // last resort before giving up.
3077  Constant *C = ConstantFoldConstant(CE, getDataLayout());
3078  if (C != CE)
3079  return lowerConstant(C);
3080 
3081  // Otherwise report the problem to the user.
3082  std::string S;
3083  raw_string_ostream OS(S);
3084  OS << "Unsupported expression in static initializer: ";
3085  CE->printAsOperand(OS, /*PrintType=*/false,
3086  !MF ? nullptr : MF->getFunction().getParent());
3087  report_fatal_error(Twine(OS.str()));
3088 }

3091  AsmPrinter &AP,
3092  const Constant *BaseCV = nullptr,
3093  uint64_t Offset = 0,
3094  AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList = nullptr);

3099 /// isRepeatedByteSequence - Determine whether the given value is
3100 /// composed of a repeated sequence of identical bytes and return the
3101 /// byte value. If it is not a repeated sequence, return -1.
3102 static int isRepeatedByteSequence(const ConstantDataSequential *V) {
3103  StringRef Data = V->getRawDataValues();
3104  assert(!Data.empty() && "Empty aggregates should be CAZ node");
3105  char C = Data[0];
3106  for (unsigned i = 1, e = Data.size(); i != e; ++i)
3107  if (Data[i] != C) return -1;
3108  return static_cast<uint8_t>(C); // Ensure 255 is not returned as -1.
3109 }
3110 
3111 /// isRepeatedByteSequence - Determine whether the given value is
3112 /// composed of a repeated sequence of identical bytes and return the
3113 /// byte value. If it is not a repeated sequence, return -1.
3114 static int isRepeatedByteSequence(const Value *V, const DataLayout &DL) {
3115  if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(V)) {
3116  uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSizeInBits(V->getType());
3117  assert(Size % 8 == 0);
3118 
3119  // Extend the element to take zero padding into account.
3120  APInt Value = CI->getValue().zext(Size);
3121  if (!Value.isSplat(8))
3122  return -1;
3123 
3124  return Value.zextOrTrunc(8).getZExtValue();
3125  }
3126  if (const ConstantArray *CA = dyn_cast<ConstantArray>(V)) {
3127  // Make sure all array elements are sequences of the same repeated
3128  // byte.
3129  assert(CA->getNumOperands() != 0 && "Should be a CAZ");
3130  Constant *Op0 = CA->getOperand(0);
3131  int Byte = isRepeatedByteSequence(Op0, DL);
3132  if (Byte == -1)
3133  return -1;
3134 
3135  // All array elements must be equal.
3136  for (unsigned i = 1, e = CA->getNumOperands(); i != e; ++i)
3137  if (CA->getOperand(i) != Op0)
3138  return -1;
3139  return Byte;
3140  }
3141 
3142  if (const ConstantDataSequential *CDS = dyn_cast<ConstantDataSequential>(V))
3143  return isRepeatedByteSequence(CDS);
3144 
3145  return -1;
3146 }

3148 static void emitGlobalAliasInline(AsmPrinter &AP, uint64_t Offset,
3149  AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) {
3150  if (AliasList) {
3151  auto AliasIt = AliasList->find(Offset);
3152  if (AliasIt != AliasList->end()) {
3153  for (const GlobalAlias *GA : AliasIt->second)
3154  AP.OutStreamer->emitLabel(AP.getSymbol(GA));
3155  AliasList->erase(Offset);
3156  }
3157  }
3158 }
3159 
3160 static void emitGlobalConstantDataSequential(
3161  const DataLayout &DL, const ConstantDataSequential *CDS, AsmPrinter &AP,
3162  AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) {
3163  // See if we can aggregate this into a .fill, if so, emit it as such.
3164  int Value = isRepeatedByteSequence(CDS, DL);
3165  if (Value != -1) {
3166  uint64_t Bytes = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getType());
3167  // Don't emit a 1-byte object as a .fill.
3168  if (Bytes > 1)
3169  return AP.OutStreamer->emitFill(Bytes, Value);
3170  }
3171 
3172  // If this can be emitted with .ascii/.asciz, emit it as such.
3173  if (CDS->isString())
3174  return AP.OutStreamer->emitBytes(CDS->getAsString());
3175 
3176  // Otherwise, emit the values in successive locations.
3177  unsigned ElementByteSize = CDS->getElementByteSize();
3178  if (isa<IntegerType>(CDS->getElementType())) {
3179  for (unsigned I = 0, E = CDS->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) {
3180  emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, ElementByteSize * I, AliasList);
3181  if (AP.isVerbose())
3182  AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS()
3183  << format("0x%" PRIx64 "\n", CDS->getElementAsInteger(I));
3184  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(CDS->getElementAsInteger(I),
3185  ElementByteSize);
3186  }
3187  } else {
3188  Type *ET = CDS->getElementType();
3189  for (unsigned I = 0, E = CDS->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) {
3190  emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, ElementByteSize * I, AliasList);
3191  emitGlobalConstantFP(CDS->getElementAsAPFloat(I), ET, AP);
3192  }
3193  }
3194 
3195  unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getType());
3196  unsigned EmittedSize =
3197  DL.getTypeAllocSize(CDS->getElementType()) * CDS->getNumElements();
3198  assert(EmittedSize <= Size && "Size cannot be less than EmittedSize!");
3199  if (unsigned Padding = Size - EmittedSize)
3200  AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(Padding);
3201 }

3203 static void emitGlobalConstantArray(const DataLayout &DL,
3204  const ConstantArray *CA, AsmPrinter &AP,
3205  const Constant *BaseCV, uint64_t Offset,
3206  AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) {
3207  // See if we can aggregate some values. Make sure it can be
3208  // represented as a series of bytes of the constant value.
3209  int Value = isRepeatedByteSequence(CA, DL);
3210 
3211  if (Value != -1) {
3212  uint64_t Bytes = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CA->getType());
3213  AP.OutStreamer->emitFill(Bytes, Value);
3214  } else {
3215  for (unsigned I = 0, E = CA->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) {
3216  emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CA->getOperand(I), AP, BaseCV, Offset,
3217  AliasList);
3218  Offset += DL.getTypeAllocSize(CA->getOperand(I)->getType());
3219  }
3220  }
3221 }

3225 static void emitGlobalConstantVector(const DataLayout &DL,
3226  const ConstantVector *CV, AsmPrinter &AP,
3227  AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) {
3228  Type *ElementType = CV->getType()->getElementType();
3229  uint64_t ElementSizeInBits = DL.getTypeSizeInBits(ElementType);
3230  uint64_t ElementAllocSizeInBits = DL.getTypeAllocSizeInBits(ElementType);
3231  uint64_t EmittedSize;
3232  if (ElementSizeInBits != ElementAllocSizeInBits) {
3233  // If the allocation size of an element is different from the size in bits,
3234  // printing each element separately will insert incorrect padding.
3235  //
3236  // The general algorithm here is complicated; instead of writing it out
3237  // here, just use the existing code in ConstantFolding.
3238  Type *IntT =
3239  IntegerType::get(CV->getContext(), DL.getTypeSizeInBits(CV->getType()));
3240  ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast_or_null<ConstantInt>(ConstantFoldConstant(
3241  ConstantExpr::getBitCast(const_cast<ConstantVector *>(CV), IntT), DL));
3242  if (!CI) {
3243  report_fatal_error(
3244  "Cannot lower vector global with unusual element type");
3245  }
3246  emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, 0, AliasList);
3247  emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(CI, AP);
3248  EmittedSize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(CV->getType());
3249  } else {
3250  for (unsigned I = 0, E = CV->getType()->getNumElements(); I != E; ++I) {
3251  emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType()) * I, AliasList);
3252  emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CV->getOperand(I), AP);
3253  }
3254  EmittedSize =
3255  DL.getTypeAllocSize(ElementType) * CV->getType()->getNumElements();
3256  }
3257 
3258  unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType());
3259  if (unsigned Padding = Size - EmittedSize)
3260  AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(Padding);
3261 }

3263 static void emitGlobalConstantStruct(const DataLayout &DL,
3264  const ConstantStruct *CS, AsmPrinter &AP,
3265  const Constant *BaseCV, uint64_t Offset,
3266  AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) {
3267  // Print the fields in successive locations. Pad to align if needed!
3268  unsigned Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CS->getType());
3269  const StructLayout *Layout = DL.getStructLayout(CS->getType());
3270  uint64_t SizeSoFar = 0;
3271  for (unsigned I = 0, E = CS->getNumOperands(); I != E; ++I) {
3272  const Constant *Field = CS->getOperand(I);
3273 
3274  // Print the actual field value.
3275  emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, Field, AP, BaseCV, Offset + SizeSoFar,
3276  AliasList);
3277 
3278  // Check if padding is needed and insert one or more 0s.
3279  uint64_t FieldSize = DL.getTypeAllocSize(Field->getType());
3280  uint64_t PadSize = ((I == E - 1 ? Size : Layout->getElementOffset(I + 1)) -
3281  Layout->getElementOffset(I)) -
3282  FieldSize;
3283  SizeSoFar += FieldSize + PadSize;
3284 
3285  // Insert padding - this may include padding to increase the size of the
3286  // current field up to the ABI size (if the struct is not packed) as well
3287  // as padding to ensure that the next field starts at the right offset.
3288  AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(PadSize);
3289  }
3290  assert(SizeSoFar == Layout->getSizeInBytes() &&
3291  "Layout of constant struct may be incorrect!");
3292 }

3294 static void emitGlobalConstantFP(APFloat APF, Type *ET, AsmPrinter &AP) {
3295  assert(ET && "Unknown float type");
3296  APInt API = APF.bitcastToAPInt();
3297 
3298  // First print a comment with what we think the original floating-point value
3299  // should have been.
3300  if (AP.isVerbose()) {
3301  SmallString<8> StrVal;
3302  APF.toString(StrVal);
3303  ET->print(AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS());
3304  AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << ' ' << StrVal << '\n';
3305  }
3306 
3307  // Now iterate through the APInt chunks, emitting them in endian-correct
3308  // order, possibly with a smaller chunk at beginning/end (e.g. for x87 80-bit
3309  // floats).
3310  unsigned NumBytes = API.getBitWidth() / 8;
3311  unsigned TrailingBytes = NumBytes % sizeof(uint64_t);
3312  const uint64_t *p = API.getRawData();
3313 
3314  // PPC's long double has odd notions of endianness compared to how LLVM
3315  // handles it: p[0] goes first for *big* endian on PPC.
3316  if (AP.getDataLayout().isBigEndian() && !ET->isPPC_FP128Ty()) {
3317  int Chunk = API.getNumWords() - 1;
3318 
3319  if (TrailingBytes)
3320  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(p[Chunk--], TrailingBytes);
3321 
3322  for (; Chunk >= 0; --Chunk)
3323  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(p[Chunk], sizeof(uint64_t));
3324  } else {
3325  unsigned Chunk;
3326  for (Chunk = 0; Chunk < NumBytes / sizeof(uint64_t); ++Chunk)
3327  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(p[Chunk], sizeof(uint64_t));
3328 
3329  if (TrailingBytes)
3330  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValueInHexWithPadding(p[Chunk], TrailingBytes);
3331  }
3332 
3333  // Emit the tail padding for the long double.
3334  const DataLayout &DL = AP.getDataLayout();
3335  AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(DL.getTypeAllocSize(ET) - DL.getTypeStoreSize(ET));
3336 }

3338 static void emitGlobalConstantFP(const ConstantFP *CFP, AsmPrinter &AP) {
3339  emitGlobalConstantFP(CFP->getValueAPF(), CFP->getType(), AP);
3340 }
3341 
3342 static void emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(const ConstantInt *CI, AsmPrinter &AP) {
3343  const DataLayout &DL = AP.getDataLayout();
3344  unsigned BitWidth = CI->getBitWidth();
3345 
3346  // Copy the value as we may massage the layout for constants whose bit width
3347  // is not a multiple of 64-bits.
3348  APInt Realigned(CI->getValue());
3349  uint64_t ExtraBits = 0;
3350  unsigned ExtraBitsSize = BitWidth & 63;
3351 
3352  if (ExtraBitsSize) {
3353  // The bit width of the data is not a multiple of 64-bits.
3354  // The extra bits are expected to be at the end of the chunk of the memory.
3355  // Little endian:
3356  // * Nothing to be done, just record the extra bits to emit.
3357  // Big endian:
3358  // * Record the extra bits to emit.
3359  // * Realign the raw data to emit the chunks of 64-bits.
3360  if (DL.isBigEndian()) {
3361  // Basically the structure of the raw data is a chunk of 64-bits cells:
3362  // 0 1 BitWidth / 64
3363  // [chunk1][chunk2] ... [chunkN].
3364  // The most significant chunk is chunkN and it should be emitted first.
3365  // However, due to the alignment issue chunkN contains useless bits.
3366  // Realign the chunks so that they contain only useful information:
3367  // ExtraBits 0 1 (BitWidth / 64) - 1
3368  // chu[nk1 chu][nk2 chu] ... [nkN-1 chunkN]
3369  ExtraBitsSize = alignTo(ExtraBitsSize, 8);
3370  ExtraBits = Realigned.getRawData()[0] &
3371  (((uint64_t)-1) >> (64 - ExtraBitsSize));
3372  Realigned.lshrInPlace(ExtraBitsSize);
3373  } else
3374  ExtraBits = Realigned.getRawData()[BitWidth / 64];
3375  }
3376 
3377  // We don't expect assemblers to support integer data directives
3378  // for more than 64 bits, so we emit the data in at most 64-bit
3379  // quantities at a time.
3380  const uint64_t *RawData = Realigned.getRawData();
3381  for (unsigned i = 0, e = BitWidth / 64; i != e; ++i) {
3382  uint64_t Val = DL.isBigEndian() ? RawData[e - i - 1] : RawData[i];
3383  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(Val, 8);
3384  }
3385 
3386  if (ExtraBitsSize) {
3387  // Emit the extra bits after the 64-bits chunks.
3388 
3389  // Emit a directive that fills the expected size.
3390  uint64_t Size = AP.getDataLayout().getTypeStoreSize(CI->getType());
3391  Size -= (BitWidth / 64) * 8;
3392  assert(Size && Size * 8 >= ExtraBitsSize &&
3393  (ExtraBits & (((uint64_t)-1) >> (64 - ExtraBitsSize)))
3394  == ExtraBits && "Directive too small for extra bits.");
3395  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(ExtraBits, Size);
3396  }
3397 }

3399 /// Transform a not absolute MCExpr containing a reference to a GOT
3400 /// equivalent global, by a target specific GOT pc relative access to the
3401 /// final symbol.
3402 static void handleIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel(AsmPrinter &AP, const MCExpr **ME,
3403  const Constant *BaseCst,
3404  uint64_t Offset) {
3405  // The global @foo below illustrates a global that uses a got equivalent.
3406  //
3407  // @bar = global i32 42
3408  // @gotequiv = private unnamed_addr constant i32* @bar
3409  // @foo = i32 trunc (i64 sub (i64 ptrtoint (i32** @gotequiv to i64),
3410  // i64 ptrtoint (i32* @foo to i64))
3411  // to i32)
3412  //
3413  // The cstexpr in @foo is converted into the MCExpr `ME`, where we actually
3414  // check whether @foo is suitable to use a GOTPCREL. `ME` is usually in the
3415  // form:
3416  //
3417  // foo = cstexpr, where
3418  // cstexpr := <gotequiv> - "." + <cst>
3419  // cstexpr := <gotequiv> - (<foo> - <offset from @foo base>) + <cst>
3420  //
3421  // After canonicalization by evaluateAsRelocatable `ME` turns into:
3422  //
3423  // cstexpr := <gotequiv> - <foo> + gotpcrelcst, where
3424  // gotpcrelcst := <offset from @foo base> + <cst>
3425  MCValue MV;
3426  if (!(*ME)->evaluateAsRelocatable(MV, nullptr, nullptr) || MV.isAbsolute())
3427  return;
3428  const MCSymbolRefExpr *SymA = MV.getSymA();
3429  if (!SymA)
3430  return;
3431 
3432  // Check that GOT equivalent symbol is cached.
3433  const MCSymbol *GOTEquivSym = &SymA->getSymbol();
3434  if (!AP.GlobalGOTEquivs.count(GOTEquivSym))
3435  return;
3436 
3437  const GlobalValue *BaseGV = dyn_cast_or_null<GlobalValue>(BaseCst);
3438  if (!BaseGV)
3439  return;
3440 
3441  // Check for a valid base symbol
3442  const MCSymbol *BaseSym = AP.getSymbol(BaseGV);
3443  const MCSymbolRefExpr *SymB = MV.getSymB();
3444 
3445  if (!SymB || BaseSym != &SymB->getSymbol())
3446  return;
3447 
3448  // Make sure to match:
3449  //
3450  // gotpcrelcst := <offset from @foo base> + <cst>
3451  //
3452  // If gotpcrelcst is positive it means that we can safely fold the pc rel
3453  // displacement into the GOTPCREL. We can also can have an extra offset <cst>
3454  // if the target knows how to encode it.
3455  int64_t GOTPCRelCst = Offset + MV.getConstant();
3456  if (GOTPCRelCst < 0)
3457  return;
3458  if (!AP.getObjFileLowering().supportGOTPCRelWithOffset() && GOTPCRelCst != 0)
3459  return;
3460 
3461  // Emit the GOT PC relative to replace the got equivalent global, i.e.:
3462  //
3463  // bar:
3464  // .long 42
3465  // gotequiv:
3466  // .quad bar
3467  // foo:
3468  // .long gotequiv - "." + <cst>
3469  //
3470  // is replaced by the target specific equivalent to:
3471  //
3472  // bar:
3473  // .long 42
3474  // foo:
3475  // .long bar@GOTPCREL+<gotpcrelcst>
3476  AsmPrinter::GOTEquivUsePair Result = AP.GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym];
3477  const GlobalVariable *GV = Result.first;
3478  int NumUses = (int)Result.second;
3479  const GlobalValue *FinalGV = dyn_cast<GlobalValue>(GV->getOperand(0));
3480  const MCSymbol *FinalSym = AP.getSymbol(FinalGV);
3481  *ME = AP.getObjFileLowering().getIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel(
3482  FinalGV, FinalSym, MV, Offset, AP.MMI, *AP.OutStreamer);
3483 
3484  // Update GOT equivalent usage information
3485  --NumUses;
3486  if (NumUses >= 0)
3487  AP.GlobalGOTEquivs[GOTEquivSym] = std::make_pair(GV, NumUses);
3488 }
3489 
3490 static void emitGlobalConstantImpl(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *CV,
3491  AsmPrinter &AP, const Constant *BaseCV,
3492  uint64_t Offset,
3493  AsmPrinter::AliasMapTy *AliasList) {
3494  emitGlobalAliasInline(AP, Offset, AliasList);
3495  uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType());
3496 
3497  // Globals with sub-elements such as combinations of arrays and structs
3498  // are handled recursively by emitGlobalConstantImpl. Keep track of the
3499  // constant symbol base and the current position with BaseCV and Offset.
3500  if (!BaseCV && CV->hasOneUse())
3501  BaseCV = dyn_cast<Constant>(CV->user_back());
3502 
3503  if (isa<ConstantAggregateZero>(CV) || isa<UndefValue>(CV))
3504  return AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(Size);
3505 
3506  if (const ConstantInt *CI = dyn_cast<ConstantInt>(CV)) {
3507  const uint64_t StoreSize = DL.getTypeStoreSize(CV->getType());
3508 
3509  if (StoreSize <= 8) {
3510  if (AP.isVerbose())
3511  AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS()
3512  << format("0x%" PRIx64 "\n", CI->getZExtValue());
3513  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(CI->getZExtValue(), StoreSize);
3514  } else {
3515  emitGlobalConstantLargeInt(CI, AP);
3516  }
3517 
3518  // Emit tail padding if needed
3519  if (Size != StoreSize)
3520  AP.OutStreamer->emitZeros(Size - StoreSize);
3521 
3522  return;
3523  }
3524 
3525  if (const ConstantFP *CFP = dyn_cast<ConstantFP>(CV))
3526  return emitGlobalConstantFP(CFP, AP);
3527 
3528  if (isa<ConstantPointerNull>(CV)) {
3529  AP.OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, Size);
3530  return;
3531  }
3532 
3533  if (const ConstantDataSequential *CDS = dyn_cast<ConstantDataSequential>(CV))
3534  return emitGlobalConstantDataSequential(DL, CDS, AP, AliasList);
3535 
3536  if (const ConstantArray *CVA = dyn_cast<ConstantArray>(CV))
3537  return emitGlobalConstantArray(DL, CVA, AP, BaseCV, Offset, AliasList);
3538 
3539  if (const ConstantStruct *CVS = dyn_cast<ConstantStruct>(CV))
3540  return emitGlobalConstantStruct(DL, CVS, AP, BaseCV, Offset, AliasList);
3541 
3542  if (const ConstantExpr *CE = dyn_cast<ConstantExpr>(CV)) {
3543  // Look through bitcasts, which might not be able to be MCExpr'ized (e.g. of
3544  // vectors).
3545  if (CE->getOpcode() == Instruction::BitCast)
3546  return emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CE->getOperand(0), AP);
3547 
3548  if (Size > 8) {
3549  // If the constant expression's size is greater than 64-bits, then we have
3550  // to emit the value in chunks. Try to constant fold the value and emit it
3551  // that way.
3552  Constant *New = ConstantFoldConstant(CE, DL);
3553  if (New != CE)
3554  return emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, New, AP);
3555  }
3556  }
3557 
3558  if (const ConstantVector *V = dyn_cast<ConstantVector>(CV))
3559  return emitGlobalConstantVector(DL, V, AP, AliasList);
3560 
3561  // Otherwise, it must be a ConstantExpr. Lower it to an MCExpr, then emit it
3562  // thread the streamer with EmitValue.
3563  const MCExpr *ME = AP.lowerConstant(CV);
3564 
3565  // Since lowerConstant already folded and got rid of all IR pointer and
3566  // integer casts, detect GOT equivalent accesses by looking into the MCExpr
3567  // directly.
3568  if (AP.getObjFileLowering().supportIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel())
3569  handleIndirectSymViaGOTPCRel(AP, &ME, BaseCV, Offset);
3570 
3571  AP.OutStreamer->emitValue(ME, Size);
3572 }
3573 
3574 /// EmitGlobalConstant - Print a general LLVM constant to the .s file.
3575 void AsmPrinter::emitGlobalConstant(const DataLayout &DL, const Constant *CV,
3576  AliasMapTy *AliasList) {
3577  uint64_t Size = DL.getTypeAllocSize(CV->getType());
3578  if (Size)
3579  emitGlobalConstantImpl(DL, CV, *this, nullptr, 0, AliasList);
3580  else if (MAI->hasSubsectionsViaSymbols()) {
3581  // If the global has zero size, emit a single byte so that two labels don't
3582  // look like they are at the same location.
3583  OutStreamer->emitIntValue(0, 1);
3584  }
3585  if (!AliasList)
3586  return;
3587  // TODO: These remaining aliases are not emitted in the correct location. Need
3588  // to handle the case where the alias offset doesn't refer to any sub-element.
3589  for (auto &AliasPair : *AliasList) {
3590  for (const GlobalAlias *GA : AliasPair.second)
3591  OutStreamer->emitLabel(getSymbol(GA));
3592  }
3593 }

3684 /// PrintParentLoopComment - Print comments about parent loops of this one.
3685 static void PrintParentLoopComment(raw_ostream &OS, const MachineLoop *Loop,
3686  unsigned FunctionNumber) {
3687  if (!Loop) return;
3688  PrintParentLoopComment(OS, Loop->getParentLoop(), FunctionNumber);
3689  OS.indent(Loop->getLoopDepth()*2)
3690  << "Parent Loop BB" << FunctionNumber << "_"
3691  << Loop->getHeader()->getNumber()

3695 /// PrintChildLoopComment - Print comments about child loops within
3696 /// the loop for this basic block, with nesting.
3697 static void PrintChildLoopComment(raw_ostream &OS, const MachineLoop *Loop,
3698  unsigned FunctionNumber) {
3699  // Add child loop information
3700  for (const MachineLoop *CL : *Loop) {
3701  OS.indent(CL->getLoopDepth()*2)
3702  << "Child Loop BB" << FunctionNumber << "_"
3703  << CL->getHeader()->getNumber() << " Depth " << CL->getLoopDepth()
3704  << '\n';
3705  PrintChildLoopComment(OS, CL, FunctionNumber);
3706  }
3707 }

3709 /// emitBasicBlockLoopComments - Pretty-print comments for basic blocks.
3710 static void emitBasicBlockLoopComments(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB,
3711  const MachineLoopInfo *LI,
3712  const AsmPrinter &AP) {
3713  // Add loop depth information
3714  const MachineLoop *Loop = LI->getLoopFor(&MBB);
3715  if (!Loop) return;
3716 
3717  MachineBasicBlock *Header = Loop->getHeader();
3718  assert(Header && "No header for loop");
3719 
3720  // If this block is not a loop header, just print out what is the loop header
3721  // and return.
3722  if (Header != &MBB) {
3723  AP.OutStreamer->AddComment(" in Loop: Header=BB" +
3724  Twine(AP.getFunctionNumber())+"_" +
3725  Twine(Loop->getHeader()->getNumber())+
3726  " Depth="+Twine(Loop->getLoopDepth()));
3727  return;
3728  }
3729 
3730  // Otherwise, it is a loop header. Print out information about child and
3731  // parent loops.
3732  raw_ostream &OS = AP.OutStreamer->getCommentOS();
3733 
3734  PrintParentLoopComment(OS, Loop->getParentLoop(), AP.getFunctionNumber());
3735 
3736  OS << "=>";
3737  OS.indent(Loop->getLoopDepth()*2-2);
3738 
3739  OS << "This ";
3740  if (Loop->isInnermost())
3741  OS << "Inner ";
3742  OS << "Loop Header: Depth=" + Twine(Loop->getLoopDepth()) << '\n';
3743 
3744  PrintChildLoopComment(OS, Loop, AP.getFunctionNumber());
3745 }

3747 /// emitBasicBlockStart - This method prints the label for the specified
3748 /// MachineBasicBlock, an alignment (if present) and a comment describing
3749 /// it if appropriate.
3750 void AsmPrinter::emitBasicBlockStart(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) {
3751  // End the previous funclet and start a new one.
3752  if (MBB.isEHFuncletEntry()) {
3753  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers) {
3754  HI.Handler->endFunclet();
3755  HI.Handler->beginFunclet(MBB);
3756  }
3757  }
3758 
3759  // Switch to a new section if this basic block must begin a section. The
3760  // entry block is always placed in the function section and is handled
3761  // separately.
3762  if (MBB.isBeginSection() && !MBB.isEntryBlock()) {
3763  OutStreamer->switchSection(
3764  getObjFileLowering().getSectionForMachineBasicBlock(MF->getFunction(),
3765  MBB, TM));
3766  CurrentSectionBeginSym = MBB.getSymbol();
3767  }
3768 
3769  // Emit an alignment directive for this block, if needed.
3770  const Align Alignment = MBB.getAlignment();
3771  if (Alignment != Align(1))
3772  emitAlignment(Alignment, nullptr, MBB.getMaxBytesForAlignment());
3773 
3774  // If the block has its address taken, emit any labels that were used to
3775  // reference the block. It is possible that there is more than one label
3776  // here, because multiple LLVM BB's may have been RAUW'd to this block after
3777  // the references were generated.
3778  if (MBB.isIRBlockAddressTaken()) {
3779  if (isVerbose())
3780  OutStreamer->AddComment("Block address taken");
3781 
3782  BasicBlock *BB = MBB.getAddressTakenIRBlock();
3783  assert(BB && BB->hasAddressTaken() && "Missing BB");
3784  for (MCSymbol *Sym : getAddrLabelSymbolToEmit(BB))
3785  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Sym);
3786  } else if (isVerbose() && MBB.isMachineBlockAddressTaken()) {
3787  OutStreamer->AddComment("Block address taken");
3788  }
3789 
3790  // Print some verbose block comments.
3791  if (isVerbose()) {
3792  if (const BasicBlock *BB = MBB.getBasicBlock()) {
3793  if (BB->hasName()) {
3794  BB->printAsOperand(OutStreamer->getCommentOS(),
3795  /*PrintType=*/false, BB->getModule());
3796  OutStreamer->getCommentOS() << '\n';
3797  }
3798  }
3799 
3800  assert(MLI != nullptr && "MachineLoopInfo should has been computed");
3801  emitBasicBlockLoopComments(MBB, MLI, *this);
3802  }
3803 
3804  // Print the main label for the block.
3805  if (shouldEmitLabelForBasicBlock(MBB)) {
3806  if (isVerbose() && MBB.hasLabelMustBeEmitted())
3807  OutStreamer->AddComment("Label of block must be emitted");
3808  OutStreamer->emitLabel(MBB.getSymbol());
3809  } else {
3810  if (isVerbose()) {
3811  // NOTE: Want this comment at start of line, don't emit with AddComment.
3812  OutStreamer->emitRawComment(" %bb." + Twine(MBB.getNumber()) + ":",
3813  false);
3814  }
3815  }
3816 
3817  if (MBB.isEHCatchretTarget() &&
3818  MAI->getExceptionHandlingType() == ExceptionHandling::WinEH) {
3819  OutStreamer->emitLabel(MBB.getEHCatchretSymbol());
3820  }
3821 
3822  // With BB sections, each basic block must handle CFI information on its own
3823  // if it begins a section (Entry block call is handled separately, next to
3824  // beginFunction).
3825  if (MBB.isBeginSection() && !MBB.isEntryBlock())
3826  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers)
3827  HI.Handler->beginBasicBlockSection(MBB);
3828 }
3829 
3830 void AsmPrinter::emitBasicBlockEnd(const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) {
3831  // Check if CFI information needs to be updated for this MBB with basic block
3832  // sections.
3833  if (MBB.isEndSection())
3834  for (const HandlerInfo &HI : Handlers)
3835  HI.Handler->endBasicBlockSection(MBB);
3836 }

3838 void AsmPrinter::emitVisibility(MCSymbol *Sym, unsigned Visibility,
3839  bool IsDefinition) const {
3840  MCSymbolAttr Attr = MCSA_Invalid;
3841 
3842  switch (Visibility) {
3843  default: break;
3844  case GlobalValue::HiddenVisibility:
3845  if (IsDefinition)
3846  Attr = MAI->getHiddenVisibilityAttr();
3847  else
3848  Attr = MAI->getHiddenDeclarationVisibilityAttr();
3849  break;
3850  case GlobalValue::ProtectedVisibility:
3851  Attr = MAI->getProtectedVisibilityAttr();
3852  break;
3853  }
3854 
3855  if (Attr != MCSA_Invalid)
3856  OutStreamer->emitSymbolAttribute(Sym, Attr);
3857 }
3858 
3859 bool AsmPrinter::shouldEmitLabelForBasicBlock(
3860  const MachineBasicBlock &MBB) const {
3861  // With `-fbasic-block-sections=`, a label is needed for every non-entry block
3862  // in the labels mode (option `=labels`) and every section beginning in the
3863  // sections mode (`=all` and `=list=`).
3864  if ((MF->hasBBLabels() || MBB.isBeginSection()) && !MBB.isEntryBlock())
3865  return true;
3866  // A label is needed for any block with at least one predecessor (when that
3867  // predecessor is not the fallthrough predecessor, or if it is an EH funclet
3868  // entry, or if a label is forced).
3869  return !MBB.pred_empty() &&
3870  (!isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthrough(&MBB) || MBB.isEHFuncletEntry() ||
3871  MBB.hasLabelMustBeEmitted());
3872 }
3873 
3874 /// isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthough - Return true if the basic block has
3875 /// exactly one predecessor and the control transfer mechanism between
3876 /// the predecessor and this block is a fall-through.
3877 bool AsmPrinter::
3878 isBlockOnlyReachableByFallthrough(const MachineBasicBlock *MBB) const {
3879  // If this is a landing pad, it isn't a fall through. If it has no preds,
3880  // then nothing falls through to it.
3881  if (MBB->isEHPad() || MBB->pred_empty())
3882  return false;
3883 
3884  // If there isn't exactly one predecessor, it can't be a fall through.
3885  if (MBB->pred_size() > 1)
3886  return false;
3887 
3888  // The predecessor has to be immediately before this block.
3889  MachineBasicBlock *Pred = *MBB->pred_begin();
3890  if (!Pred->isLayoutSuccessor(MBB))
3891  return false;
3892 
3893  // If the block is completely empty, then it definitely does fall through.
3894  if (Pred->empty())
3895  return true;
3896 
3897  // Check the terminators in the previous blocks
3898  for (const auto &MI : Pred->terminators()) {
3899  // If it is not a simple branch, we are in a table somewhere.
3900  if (!MI.isBranch() || MI.isIndirectBranch())
3901  return false;
3902 
3903  // If we are the operands of one of the branches, this is not a fall
3904  // through. Note that targets with delay slots will usually bundle
3905  // terminators with the delay slot instruction.
3906  for (ConstMIBundleOperands OP(MI); OP.isValid(); ++OP) {
3907  if (OP->isJTI())
3908  return false;
3909  if (OP->isMBB() && OP->getMBB() == MBB)
3910  return false;
3911  }
3912  }
3913 
3914  return true;
3915 }
3916 
3917 GCMetadataPrinter *AsmPrinter::getOrCreateGCPrinter(GCStrategy &S) {
3918  if (!S.usesMetadata())
3919  return nullptr;
3920 
3921  auto [GCPI, Inserted] = GCMetadataPrinters.insert({&S, nullptr});
3922  if (!Inserted)
3923  return GCPI->second.get();
3924 
3925  auto Name = S.getName();
3926 
3927  for (const GCMetadataPrinterRegistry::entry &GCMetaPrinter :
3928  GCMetadataPrinterRegistry::entries())
3929  if (Name == GCMetaPrinter.getName()) {
3930  std::unique_ptr<GCMetadataPrinter> GMP = GCMetaPrinter.instantiate();
3931  GMP->S = &S;
3932  GCPI->second = std::move(GMP);
3933  return GCPI->second.get();
3934  }
3935 
3936  report_fatal_error("no GCMetadataPrinter registered for GC: " + Twine(Name));
3937 }

3939 void AsmPrinter::emitStackMaps() {
3940  GCModuleInfo *MI = getAnalysisIfAvailable<GCModuleInfo>();
3941  assert(MI && "AsmPrinter didn't require GCModuleInfo?");
3942  bool NeedsDefault = false;
3943  if (MI->begin() == MI->end())
3944  // No GC strategy, use the default format.
3945  NeedsDefault = true;
3946  else
3947  for (const auto &I : *MI) {
3948  if (GCMetadataPrinter *MP = getOrCreateGCPrinter(*I))
3949  if (MP->emitStackMaps(SM, *this))
3950  continue;
3951  // The strategy doesn't have printer or doesn't emit custom stack maps.
3952  // Use the default format.
3953  NeedsDefault = true;
3954  }
3955 
3956  if (NeedsDefault)
3957  SM.serializeToStackMapSection();
3958 }

3965 // In the binary's "xray_instr_map" section, an array of these function entries
3966 // describes each instrumentation point. When XRay patches your code, the index
3967 // into this table will be given to your handler as a patch point identifier.
3968 void AsmPrinter::XRayFunctionEntry::emit(int Bytes, MCStreamer *Out) const {
3969  auto Kind8 = static_cast<uint8_t>(Kind);
3970  Out->emitBinaryData(StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&Kind8), 1));
3971  Out->emitBinaryData(
3972  StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&AlwaysInstrument), 1));
3973  Out->emitBinaryData(StringRef(reinterpret_cast<const char *>(&Version), 1));
3974  auto Padding = (4 * Bytes) - ((2 * Bytes) + 3);
3975  assert(Padding >= 0 && "Instrumentation map entry > 4 * Word Size");
3976  Out->emitZeros(Padding);
3977 }
3978 
3979 void AsmPrinter::emitXRayTable() {
3980  if (Sleds.empty())
3981  return;
3982 
3983  auto PrevSection = OutStreamer->getCurrentSectionOnly();
3984  const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
3985  MCSection *InstMap = nullptr;
3986  MCSection *FnSledIndex = nullptr;
3987  const Triple &TT = TM.getTargetTriple();
3988  // Use PC-relative addresses on all targets.
3989  if (TT.isOSBinFormatELF()) {
3990  auto LinkedToSym = cast<MCSymbolELF>(CurrentFnSym);
3991  auto Flags = ELF::SHF_ALLOC | ELF::SHF_LINK_ORDER;
3992  StringRef GroupName;
3993  if (F.hasComdat()) {
3994  Flags |= ELF::SHF_GROUP;
3995  GroupName = F.getComdat()->getName();
3996  }
3997  InstMap = OutContext.getELFSection("xray_instr_map", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS,
3998  Flags, 0, GroupName, F.hasComdat(),
3999  MCSection::NonUniqueID, LinkedToSym);
4000 
4001  if (!TM.Options.XRayOmitFunctionIndex)
4002  FnSledIndex = OutContext.getELFSection(
4003  "xray_fn_idx", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, Flags | ELF::SHF_WRITE, 0,
4004  GroupName, F.hasComdat(), MCSection::NonUniqueID, LinkedToSym);
4005  } else if (MF->getSubtarget().getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatMachO()) {
4006  InstMap = OutContext.getMachOSection("__DATA", "xray_instr_map", 0,
4007  SectionKind::getReadOnlyWithRel());
4008  if (!TM.Options.XRayOmitFunctionIndex)
4009  FnSledIndex = OutContext.getMachOSection(
4010  "__DATA", "xray_fn_idx", 0, SectionKind::getReadOnlyWithRel());
4011  } else {
4012  llvm_unreachable("Unsupported target");
4013  }
4014 
4015  auto WordSizeBytes = MAI->getCodePointerSize();
4016 
4017  // Now we switch to the instrumentation map section. Because this is done
4018  // per-function, we are able to create an index entry that will represent the
4019  // range of sleds associated with a function.
4020  auto &Ctx = OutContext;
4021  MCSymbol *SledsStart = OutContext.createTempSymbol("xray_sleds_start", true);
4022  OutStreamer->switchSection(InstMap);
4023  OutStreamer->emitLabel(SledsStart);
4024  for (const auto &Sled : Sleds) {
4025  MCSymbol *Dot = Ctx.createTempSymbol();
4026  OutStreamer->emitLabel(Dot);
4027  OutStreamer->emitValueImpl(
4028  MCBinaryExpr::createSub(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Sled.Sled, Ctx),
4029  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Dot, Ctx), Ctx),
4030  WordSizeBytes);
4031  OutStreamer->emitValueImpl(
4032  MCBinaryExpr::createSub(
4033  MCSymbolRefExpr::create(CurrentFnBegin, Ctx),
4034  MCBinaryExpr::createAdd(MCSymbolRefExpr::create(Dot, Ctx),
4035  MCConstantExpr::create(WordSizeBytes, Ctx),
4036  Ctx),
4037  Ctx),
4038  WordSizeBytes);
4039  Sled.emit(WordSizeBytes, OutStreamer.get());
4040  }
4041  MCSymbol *SledsEnd = OutContext.createTempSymbol("xray_sleds_end", true);
4042  OutStreamer->emitLabel(SledsEnd);
4043 
4044  // We then emit a single entry in the index per function. We use the symbols
4045  // that bound the instrumentation map as the range for a specific function.
4046  // Each entry here will be 2 * word size aligned, as we're writing down two
4047  // pointers. This should work for both 32-bit and 64-bit platforms.
4048  if (FnSledIndex) {
4049  OutStreamer->switchSection(FnSledIndex);
4050  OutStreamer->emitCodeAlignment(Align(2 * WordSizeBytes),
4051  &getSubtargetInfo());
4052  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(SledsStart, WordSizeBytes, false);
4053  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(SledsEnd, WordSizeBytes, false);
4054  OutStreamer->switchSection(PrevSection);
4055  }
4056  Sleds.clear();
4057 }
4058 
4059 void AsmPrinter::recordSled(MCSymbol *Sled, const MachineInstr &MI,
4060  SledKind Kind, uint8_t Version) {
4061  const Function &F = MI.getMF()->getFunction();
4062  auto Attr = F.getFnAttribute("function-instrument");
4063  bool LogArgs = F.hasFnAttribute("xray-log-args");
4064  bool AlwaysInstrument =
4065  Attr.isStringAttribute() && Attr.getValueAsString() == "xray-always";
4066  if (Kind == SledKind::FUNCTION_ENTER && LogArgs)
4067  Kind = SledKind::LOG_ARGS_ENTER;
4068  Sleds.emplace_back(XRayFunctionEntry{Sled, CurrentFnSym, Kind,
4069  AlwaysInstrument, &F, Version});
4070 }
4071 
4072 void AsmPrinter::emitPatchableFunctionEntries() {
4073  const Function &F = MF->getFunction();
4074  unsigned PatchableFunctionPrefix = 0, PatchableFunctionEntry = 0;
4075  (void)F.getFnAttribute("patchable-function-prefix")
4076  .getValueAsString()
4077  .getAsInteger(10, PatchableFunctionPrefix);
4078  (void)F.getFnAttribute("patchable-function-entry")
4079  .getValueAsString()
4080  .getAsInteger(10, PatchableFunctionEntry);
4081  if (!PatchableFunctionPrefix && !PatchableFunctionEntry)
4082  return;
4083  const unsigned PointerSize = getPointerSize();
4084  if (TM.getTargetTriple().isOSBinFormatELF()) {
4085  auto Flags = ELF::SHF_WRITE | ELF::SHF_ALLOC;
4086  const MCSymbolELF *LinkedToSym = nullptr;
4087  StringRef GroupName;
4088 
4089  // GNU as < 2.35 did not support section flag 'o'. GNU ld < 2.36 did not
4090  // support mixed SHF_LINK_ORDER and non-SHF_LINK_ORDER sections.
4091  if (MAI->useIntegratedAssembler() || MAI->binutilsIsAtLeast(2, 36)) {
4092  Flags |= ELF::SHF_LINK_ORDER;
4093  if (F.hasComdat()) {
4094  Flags |= ELF::SHF_GROUP;
4095  GroupName = F.getComdat()->getName();
4096  }
4097  LinkedToSym = cast<MCSymbolELF>(CurrentFnSym);
4098  }
4099  OutStreamer->switchSection(OutContext.getELFSection(
4100  "__patchable_function_entries", ELF::SHT_PROGBITS, Flags, 0, GroupName,
4101  F.hasComdat(), MCSection::NonUniqueID, LinkedToSym));
4102  emitAlignment(Align(PointerSize));
4103  OutStreamer->emitSymbolValue(CurrentPatchableFunctionEntrySym, PointerSize);
4104  }
4105 }
